title: sweet and sour sauce(for cocktail wieners)
directions: Mix and simmer until jelly is dissolved and thickened.
Add cocktail wieners and heat through.
Serve warm.

title: pickle sandwich
directions: *Can use lo-cal or Neufchatel cheese.

title: delicious fruit dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Use as a dip for cantaloupe chunks, strawberries, grapes or any fruit.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Combine caramel candies with heavy cream in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water, stirring frequently, until well blended.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar and flour; cook until it begins to thicken. Let cool for a short time.
Add egg yolks slowly.
Add coconut. Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine. Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until crust is done.
Add meringue and brown.

title: meat loaf and gravy
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients thoroughly.
Divide mixture and place equal portions in 2 greased 4 x 8-inch loaf pans.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Slowly add flour, stirring constantly. Add water, milk, drippings and beef base and continue stirring until well heated.
Do not boil.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix together until most of the ice cream is melted.
Best if ice cream is soft.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir boiling water into cornmeal; continue stirring until mixture is lukewarm.
Blend 1 tablespoon margarine and egg yolks.
Stir in buttermilk, salt, sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with margarine.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough boiling water to make 2 cups.
Dissolve gelatin in this liquid.
Add sherbet and stir until melted.
Add fruit and chill.

title: pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops and brown.
Mix all remaining ingredients together and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Or put potatoes and chops in crock-pot; let cook on high about 2 to 3 hours, then turn to low until supper time.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let set for a short while before removing them from the cookie sheet.

title: rice-n-beans
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until soft.
(I use olive oil.) Add tomatoes, zucchini and oregano.
Cover skillet and simmer about 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add the beans and simmer mixture, stirring occasionally, until heated through.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve over hot rice and sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: brown front stone cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour and salt.
Stir cocoa in warm water.
Allow to cool and pour in soda.
To creamed mixture, add sifted flour and salt alternately with cocoa mixture and buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: easiest chili ever
directions: Brown and crumble beef in skillet. Drain.
While beef cooks, put other ingredients into slow cooker in order given.
Add cooked, drained beef.
Stir.
Cover and cook 4 to 5 hours on high or 8 to 10 hours on low.
It won't hurt it if it cooks longer, up to 6 hours on high or 12 on low is okay.

title: stove top chicken casserole
directions: Cut onion and celery.
Put in pot with chicken.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Debone chicken.
Cook rice according to directions.
Put rice in 13 x 9 pan, then add chicken.
Add can of mushrooms.
Mix can of mushroom soup with 1/2 can of chicken broth.
Pour over mushrooms.
Do the same with chicken and celery soup.
Put onion and celery that was cooked with chicken on top of soups.
Mix Stove Top dressing with chicken stock and put on top of other layers.
Cook at 375° until bubbly and brown.

title: hot virginia dip
directions: Saute pecans in the margarine; set aside.
Combine and mix remaining ingredients.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with sauteed pecans.
Cover and chill.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, covered.
Serve with crackers.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour and extract.
Put in a greased or Pammed jelly roll pan.
Spoon filling in (1 tablespoon in each of 24 serving pieces).
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes.
You may cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring butter, sugar, milk and cocoa to a boil for 1/2 minute. Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let stand to set.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Shell shrimp.
Wash, devein and dry. Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with nonfat spray.
Mix together liquid Butter Buds, salt, garlic and 2 tablespoons parsley.
Pour into baking dish.
Arrange shrimp in a single layer.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, lemon peel and rest of parsley.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Less baking time if using smaller shrimp.
Spoon mixture over cooked rice or noodles.
Use bread to soak up sauce.

title: chicken combo casserole
directions: Combine.
Spread into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Crumble topping over meat mixture.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and scrape squash.
Cut into slices.
Place in dish, uncooked or cooked.
If cooked, cook with onion and place a layer of squash and onion in greased baking dish.
Top layer with cracker crumbs and salt and dot with butter and add grated cheese.
Build layers until 3 fold layers are built.
Top with cheese.
Before placing in 350° oven add enough water to keep from being too dry or burning.
When cheese melts and casserole is bubbly, it is ready to serve.
Will serve 6 to 8 folks.

title: cheese angel biscuits
directions: Combine yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk; set aside.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cut in shortening until it resembles coarse meal.
Stir in cheese.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture; stir only until moist.
Cover and chill for 30 minutes. Make into biscuits.
Cover; let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: bonnie's bean dip(appetizer)
directions: Put everything, except the grated cheeses, into the crock-pot. Mix well.
Put the grated cheeses on top.
Heat on low in the crock-pot until all the cheeses are melted.
Stir carefully. You can leave the dip in the heating crock-pot while it is being served.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: If using cake mix, bake cake as directed.
Cool.
Break either cake being used into pieces.
Place 1/2 of chunks into punch bowl. Put 1/2 of prepared pudding over cake, then put a layer of bananas.
Next, put 1/2 of pineapple (don't drain).
Follow with 1/2 of cherries or strawberries, juice included.
Now carefully spread 1/2 of Cool Whip on.
Repeat layers all again starting with cake and ending with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and maraschino cherries.
Best when let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: chinese apricot topping(for egg rolls and wontons)
directions: If you want it more sour, add more sweet and sour sauce. Simmer on stove about 10 minutes.

title: herb roast
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar with mixer.
Blend the rest by hand and add to cream cheese and sugar.
Freeze in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex loaf pan.
Set out 15 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve. Cover with plastic wrap or foil before freezing.

title: chilled strawberry soup
directions: Reserve 2 strawberries for garnish.
In a bowl of a food processor fitted with a metal wing blade or in a jar of an electric blender, place strawberries, yogurt, milk, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla extract.
Cover and whirl until strawberries are pureed and mixture is combined.
Chill in a covered container until ready to serve.
Slice reserved strawberries; use to garnish soup.
Serve with a mixed green salad.
Yield:
3 cups, 3 portions.

title: dream pie
directions: Beat whipped topping.
Mix with 1 cup of milk and vanilla, using a large bowl.
Beat on high about 6 minutes or until topping thickens.
Add 1 3/4 cups of milk and pudding mix; blend at low speed.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Spoon into pie shell; chill at least 4 hours.

title: barley soup
directions: Simmer barley in 1/2 of stock until tender.
Add butter gradually.
Boil chopped vegetables until tender in remaining stock, then add cooked barley and seasoning.
When ready to serve, add sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: microwave quick and easy brownies
directions: Place chocolate and butter in 2-quart casserole.
Heat for 3 to 4 minutes until mixture is melted.
Stir 2 or 3 times during melting.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend well and stir in nuts. Spread evenly in greased 8-inch round dish.
(Deep pie plate works great.)
Bake for 6 or 7 minutes or until top springs back when lightly pressed.
Turn dish halfway through cooking time.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rub large wooden bowl with cut clove of garlic.
Allow a few small pieces of garlic to remain in bowl.
Mix anchovies, oil, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt, mustard and pepper in bowl.
Add romaine and toss until leaves are coated.
Sprinkle with croutons and cheese and toss.
Serves 6.
Each serving has 180 calories.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 8-inch pie plate.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs; blend in sugar and butter.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts if desired.
Pour into prepared pie plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until almost set (pie will not test done in center).
Cool; cut into wedges.
Serve topped with ice cream and hot fudge.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pasta stew(vegetarian)
directions: In a large pot, saute the onion and garlic in a small amount of water until soft.
Add the tomatoes, tomato sauce, zucchini, corn, beans and seasonings.
Cook for about 15 minutes.
Add spaghetti and cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add the greens and stir until wilted.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chop suey cupcakes
directions: In saucepan, combine first 8 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil together for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder together and add to cooled mixture.
Blend in vanilla.

title: squash and sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain and put aside. In skillet, cook squash, tomato and onion in oil until tender (not mushy). Layer squash in a casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and crumbs. Place sausage on top. Pour tomato paste and water all over. Bake at 325° about 30 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Drop in meat balls and simmer 1 half hour, stirring often in a larger pot.

title: sweet relish
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime and water for 24 hours.
Then drain the cucumbers and rinse well.
Soak for 3 hours in enough cold water to cover.
Drain again and rinse well. Mix the rest of ingredients and pour over the cucumbers.
Let stand overnight.

title: one-apiece meat loaves
directions: Peel cucumber.
Cut cucumber lengthwise in half.
Using spoon, scoop out seeds from each cucumber half.
Coarsely shred enough cucumber to make 1 cup.
Slice remaining cucumber to use as garnish.
In medium bowl, combine cucumber, ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and egg.
Divide meat mixture into 4 portions.
Unwrap 4 cheese slices; fold each into 1 1/2 x 3/4 x 1/2-inch chunks.
Shape each portion of meat around 1 chunk of cheese, making 4 x 2-inch oval loaves.
Arrange loaves in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover dish with wax paper.
Cook at Medium-high (70% power) for 9 minutes.
Remove wax paper, rotating dish a half turn; top each loaf with a slice of cheese.
Cook at Medium-high for 2 minutes longer.
Let meat loaves stand for 3 minutes.
Remove from baking dish and arrange on warm plate. Garnish with cucumber slices.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: oven fried chicken and gravy(low-fat and diabetic)
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Combine crushed corn flakes, paprika and powders.
Roll chicken in milk.
Roll chicken in corn flakes.
Place chicken in small baking dish sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: double chocolate chip cookies(allan's favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour and soda in a small bowl. In large bowl, cream together butter, sugars and vanilla.
Whisk in egg.
Stir in cocoa and milk.
Fold in flour, walnuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto nonstick baking sheet.
Bake for about 12 minutes.
Cool about 5 minutes before removing cookies from sheets.

title: carrot fritters
directions: Boil carrots and mash like potatoes.
Add eggs, cinnamon and enough flour to thicken; drop in hot grease as you would hush puppies.
Fry for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Very good.

title: cocktail dogs
directions: Slice hotdogs into 2 slices. Place in medium saucepan. Combine jelly, BBQ sauce,
mustard and brown sugar. Pour over hotdogs and simmer for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Sift sugar, jello, and cornstarch together.
Add 4 cups cold water; mix real good.
Cook until thick or until it comes to a boil; do not over cook.
Cool completely.
Put strawberries in crust then pour jello mixture over berries.
Before serving put Cool Whip on top.

title: dill onion rings
directions: Peel and cut onion into thin crosswise slices.
Separate into rings.
Place in small bowl. Combine vinegar, water, salt, dill weed and sugar in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over onion rings; cover tightly and chill at least 1 hour to blend flavors. The liquid can be reheated and used on another onion.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° until done.

title: cheese and potato wild rice soup
directions: Fry bacon and onions until bacon is crisp.
Drain excess fat. Place soup in saucepan and heat.
Stir in half and half, bacon, onions, cheese and cooked wild rice.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Cut one roll of cookies into 28 slices.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan with cookies.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth; pour over cookies. Cut second roll of cookies into 24 slices; place on top of mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: beef barcelona
directions: Brown a 3 to 4 pound pot roast in 1/4 cup dressing.
Add remaining dressing and 1/2 cup water.
Cover and cook slowly for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add stuffed olives, onions and potatoes.
Cook 45 minutes more or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: liz's white pizza pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread Ricotta cheese onto pizza crust (we like a lot of it).
Then add Mozzarella, Parmesan, oregano, garlic and black pepper.
Sprinkle olive oil last.
Bake until cheeses are melted.
Delicious!

title: carrie anne's peanut butter surprise
directions: Microwave peanut butter about 40 seconds; this helps to mix up with other ingredients.
Mix well all ingredients.

You can make into little balls, using orange food coloring and topping with chocolate morsels to make pumpkins for Halloween or Thanksgiving or green food coloring to make wreaths or Christmas trees using small cookie cutters to make nice Christmas treats.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: tiny ham puffs
directions: In mixing bowl, combine ham, celery, chutney, mayonnaise and pepper; mix well.
Chill.
In small saucepan, heat water to boiling.
Add crumbled pie crust mix; stir vigorously over low heat until pastry forms a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Cook 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add eggs and beat on low speed, electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° until golden brown and dry, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Split puffs.
Just before serving, fill with chilled ham mixture. Makes 42 puffs.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add crushed potato chips and pecans.
Stir in flour.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press ball flat with bottom of tumbler dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill for a few hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: grown up cranberry glog
directions: Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag; place in a saucepan.
Add 2 cups juice and sugar; bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 10 minutes.
Remove spices; cool.
Can sit for about 1 to 2 hours.
Before serving, add remaining juice and wine; heat to almost boiling.
Serve warm and enjoy!
This is great on a cold, dreary day.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: grilled pork tenderloins
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl with wire whisk until well blended.
Coat meat thoroughly.
Place in covered bowl in refrigerator for several hours.
Grill over hot coals, approximately 20 minutes per side.
Baste frequently with sauce while cooking.
Serve with Jezebel Sauce.
Three tenderloins serve 8 people!
Double recipe for 3 tenderloins.

title: carrot soup
directions: Chop bacon and brown.
Add chopped onion with 1 1/2 tablespoons butter; cook until onion is limp.
Add water and bouillon cubes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in egg; coat with bread crumb mixture.
Brown chicken in butter on both sides.
Put chicken in baking dish.
Cover with green pepper.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add all of 20 ounce can crushed pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients by hand not mixer. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage and set aside.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, roll out crescent rolls and close up perforation marks.
Spread sausage evenly over dough.
Mix eggs and milk together and spread over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave fondue
directions: In a medium-sized bowl, combine cheese, flour and nutmeg, tossing well to mix.
Set aside.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cut a pocket in each chicken breast by laying flat and cut from side to side.
Roll half of ham in a slice of cheese.
Stuff ham and cheese roll in chicken pocket.
Follow Shake 'n Bake recipe (roll in mix and bake).
Allow a couple of minutes extra baking time.
Makes 2 servings.

title: little smokies
directions: Combine jelly and chili sauce until smooth texture.
Pour over wieners.
Heat on low in crock-pot until bubbly.
Do not overheat or wieners will become rubbery.

title: texas style lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat; drain.
Add seasoned salt, taco seasoning, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chilies.
Mix well. Simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and eggs.

title: egg casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place 1/2 the bread on bottom; cover with cooked ham.
Cover ham with Cheddar and Jack cheeses; cover Cheddar and Jack cheese with chilies.
Top with remainder of bread.
Make custard out of milk, eggs and spices; beat well with mixer.
Pour egg batter over bread.
Cover with plastic wrap; put in refrigerator overnight.

title: salsa ranchero
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix in short intervals, being careful not to let ingredients become watery.
Will stay fresh in refrigerator in covered container for 2 weeks.

title: whole wheat-buttermilk biscuits
directions: For cheese biscuits, add 1/2 cup packed, grated cheese.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash zucchini and cut into thin slices.
Peel and cut onions into quarters and then slice very thin.
Add to water and add salt.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain throughly.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over zucchini and onions.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Bring all ingredients to a boil for 5 minutes.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients fine and mix well. For milder salsa, remove seeds from chilies.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook noodles in broth where chicken was cooked.
Add Velveeta while still hot.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add all ingredients to noodles broth mixture.
This makes one large casserole or two small ones.
Freezes well at this point.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea skillet supper
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet, crumbling with fork as cooks. Drain fat; add green peppers, onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes. Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Stir well.
Add peas with liquid. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve hot with cheese sprinkled on top.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients and put in unbaked pastry shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate kahlua cake
directions: Combine cake and pudding mixes, chocolate chips, sour cream, eggs, kahlua and oil; mix by hand until well blended.
Pour into Bundt pan, bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not overbake. Let stand for 20 minutes, then remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: delicious string bean casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add celery and onion and cook until tender. Drain beans.
Add beans and pimento to onion and celery.
Mix juice from beans with soup.
Add to bean mixture and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and then cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: german casserole(great winter dish)
directions: Saute cabbage and onion in margarine until tender with salt and pepper. Lay drained potatoes on top of cabbage and onion. Sprinkle caraway seed next.
Crumble raw hamburger on top of vegetables.
(If adding kielbasa, do so now.) Cover all with tomato sauce.
(If mixture looks too dry, add 1/2 tomato sauce can of water.)
Cover with lid and simmer on low for 1 hour.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to first mixture alternately with milk.
Add well-floured nuts and almonds.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites to which salt has been added.
Bake in cupcake or mini cupcake pans at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barbecue taco salads
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Heat thoroughly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet or stockpot. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover and simmer on low, stirring occasionally, until beans are tender (about 3 hours). Add water occasionally, as needed.
(If you are in a hurry, follow the directions, except leave out the beans and simmer about 45 minutes, then add 1 can kidney beans, drained, and simmer an additional 15 minutes.)

title: cucumber freeze
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions in salt water 2 hours (1/2 cup salt to 1 gallon water or 3 quarts).
Drain; rinse.
Boil sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Cool slightly.
Pour over cucumbers. Mix.
Freeze for 5 days.

title: praline cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add molasses and egg; mix well.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in butterscotch pieces.
Chill in refrigerator two hours.
Form into approximately 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Top each with a pecan half.
Bake in a 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes.

title: marinade for beef
directions: Use beef stew meat, round steak or flank steak.
Mix marinade ingredients and add meat in a shallow container or plastic Ziploc bag.
Marinade meat in refrigerator at least 1 1/2 hours.
Skewer beef stew with various vegetables; barbecue.
(Or barbecue steak until desired doneness.) Discard marinade.

title: apple tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil. Cool. May be stored in refrigerator for several weeks.
Heat as needed in desired amounts.

title: crisp spicy molasses cookies
directions: Blend Spry, salt and spices, then add sugar and cream.
Add eggs and beat.
Add molasses and mix.
Add flour and soda to this mixture.
Drop from tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with damp cloth-covered glass.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hamburger tater casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer hamburger loosely. Layer a thinly sliced onion.
Add a layer of peas, thawed and drained.
Pour over all 1 can of soup.
Top with cheese. Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: caramel rolls
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, butter, vanilla ice cream, brown sugar and vanilla.
Cut up biscuits into quarters.
Roll each piece in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and pour melted mixture over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and onion until water is evaporated.
Add soup and Velveeta.
Heat until cheese melts.
Bob's favorite!

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Mash artichoke hearts with potato masher until fairly smooth. Mix Parmesan and mayonnaise together well and add to mashed artichoke hearts.
Place mixture into a small ovenproof casserole dish and bake at 350° until top turns light brown and bubbly. Serve warm with Triscuits crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash in 2 cups water until tender.
Drain and mash squash and drain again.
Add 1/2 stick oleo (melted), 2 beaten eggs and 1 cup grated sharp Cheddar cheese and mix.

title: chicken pie(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine. Add flour, soup, milk and broth. Add chicken and cook until mixture thickens.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Combine crumbs and salt.
Dip chicken pieces in milk and coat with crumbs.
Place in a single layer, skin side up, in a greased, foil-lined, shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with butter or olive oil.

title: italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in saucepan and cover with water. Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes. Transfer to baking dish.
Pour entire bottle of salad dressing over chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Use as a vegetable dip.

title: seafarer scallops with pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Do not overcook. Drain, set aside and keep warm.

title: barbecue sauce in large quantity
directions: Simmer ingredients for 5 hours. This sauce may be bottled and frozen. Makes about 2 gallons.

title: hamburger vegetable chowder
directions: Brown hamburger in oil over medium heat; add all other ingredients except rice.
Cook on low for one hour then add rice. Cook until rice is done.
Add more water or tomato juice if liquid is too thick.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream. Mix thoroughly.

title: mama's plain pickles
directions: This recipe makes 7 pints.
Pack cucumbers in pint jars.
Mix other ingredients; bring to a boil, approximately 5 to 10 minutes. Pour over cucumbers; seal jars.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/2 cup milk and melted butter together. Put 1/2 batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt the butter in an oblong pan.
Make layer of graham crackers.
Mix remaining ingredients; place on top of graham crackers.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: mexican burgers
directions: Heat broiler or prepare outdoor grill.
In a large bowl, combine beef, salsa, scallions, garlic, cumin, coriander, salt and pepper.
Mix to blend well.
Divide mixture in fourths, shaping each portion into a long oval patty about 1 1/4-inch thick.
Place patties on grill, broiler pan or a foil lined cookie sheet and cook until done (5 to 6 minutes per side for medium).
Meanwhile, wrap the tortillas in foil.

Place them away from the heat on a cooler part of grill or the bottom rack of oven to warm, 3 to 5 minutes. To assemble, place patties on warmed tortillas and top each with 2 tablespoons cheese and some shredded lettuce.
Serve with sliced avocado and olives if desired.
Serves 4.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Also, add other ingredients such as vanilla, etc. Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: never fail cooked rice
directions: Measure rice exactly and put in a fine mesh wire strainer. Under cold running water, rub rice against the sides of strainer until water comes out clear.
Or put into a pan and wash with your hands changing water 4 times; drain.
Put water and salt in 1 to 2 quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, add rice and bring to a boil for 1 minute and lower heat to medium-low.
Cover and cook 25 minutes. Don't lift lid to peek.
Use a plate if you don't have a lid. Remove from heat.
Lift lid and fluff with a fork.
Serve.

title: cherry pie
directions: Pour whole can of
pineapple
and
juice into bottom of large Pyrex dish and
spread
evenly.
Add
cherry pie filling over top of pineapple. Add
dry
cake
mix over top of mixture evenly. Take 2 sticks
of margarine and cut into thin slices; place in rows over mixture.	Sprinkle with nuts.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Wash berries (pick out stems).
In a heavy saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce to moderate heat. Cook, stirring constantly, for 10 to 12 minutes, until mixture is thick.
Pour into 4-cup mold rinsed with cold water. Refrigerate 4 hours or longer until mold is very firm.
To release, run knife around edge. Dip bottom briefly in hot water and invert over plate.
Garnish with fruit slices and pecans.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line baking dish with dried beef.
Wrap 6 boned chicken breasts with strip of bacon.
Lay on top of beef.

title: leona adams's chicken dumplings
directions: Put 1 tablespoon of salt on chicken and cover with water. Cook until tender.
Remove meat from the bones and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in a bowl with hot chicken broth.
Make 5 portions of dough; roll real thin and cut into strips.
Pull off pieces about 3 inches long.
Drop into boiling broth.
Keep broth boiling until all dough is added.
If you need more broth, add hot water. Add chicken and boil 3 minutes.

title: butter bars
directions: In a bowl, mix together all the ingredients. Press into a greased 9 x 11 pan. Set aside.

title: spicy cranberry-orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in large bowl. Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice and cinnamon. Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in orange. Spoon into 5-cup mold.
Refrigerate about 4 hours or until firm. Unmold.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into large baking dish. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: *Use liquids from mushrooms and olives as part of the liquid.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine the 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and bread cubes in microwavable 1 1/2-quart dish or casserole.
In medium mixing bowl, blend eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Set both of these aside.
In microwavable measuring cup, combine milk and butter and microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes until scalding.
Pour slowly, stirring into the egg mixture, then pour all over the bread cubes. Cover dish with wax paper.
Microwave on Medium for 15 to 17 minutes.
Every 5 minutes push the edges to center with spatula. Let it stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Can be topped with whipped cream or lemon sauce.
(See Daffodil Lemon Sauce recipe.)

title: white chocolate red raspberry pie
directions: Whip whipping cream in electric mixer until soft peaks are formed and place in refrigerator to remain cool.
Melt 4 ounces of white chocolate with 2 tablespoons milk in microwave for 1 minute. Stir to blend and set aside to cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and grated orange peel in electric mixer.
Add melted white chocolate.	Fold in whipped cream and place in a baked pie crust that has been cooled.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: To
1/4 cup mashed potatoes add powdered sugar gradually, mixing
well until well blended and about the texture and consistency
of
pie
dough that can be rolled out. (Approximately
pound
powdered
sugar.)
Roll
out and spread with peanut butter
or
caramel.
Roll
up
as for a jelly roll and slice after chilling.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: Saute diced garlic in 1 tablespoon lite oil. Add onion and pepper.
Saute 5 to 10 minutes. Add chicken broth and tomatoes. Let simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Add capers.
Add chicken chunks and let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over nest of cooked angel hair pasta.

title: chocolate chip ice cream pie
directions: Lightly coat bottom and sides of an 8-inch pie plate with butter.
Combine chocolate syrup and chocolate chips in a small microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on HIGH until hot, about 30-45 seconds.
Stir until smooth.
Reserve 1/4 cup of this chocolate mixture.

title: mock pralines
directions: Place butter, margarine and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Butter cookie sheet and line with graham cracker squares.
Pour boiled mixture over crackers and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let cool for 5 minutes, then break into pieces.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat olive oil and butter in a 12 inch skillet over medium heat, add onions and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix drained Veg-All with other ingredients.
Pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: easter bread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar slowly.
Add vanilla and anise.
In large pan, put flour, salt.
Add liquid ingredients.
Add oil.
Knead 20 mins.
If sticky, add oil to hands.
Let rise 2 1/2 -3 hours. Punch down.
Let rise again 1 1/2 hours. shape loaves.
Let rise 1 more hour.
Brush with beaten egg mixed with sugar.
Bake 325° for 30 mins.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Dissolve baking soda in milk; add to banana and mix.
Then add to creamed ingredients. Mix flour and baking powder thoroughly, then add to rest of ingredients.
Grease loaf pans (2) and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Heat fat and cook pepper until tender.
Blend the flour into fat.
Blend in broth and milk.
Stir in the chicken and cook to a smooth sauce.
Stir.
Serve on cooked rice, toast or biscuits.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs. Beat well. Add bananas and lemon juice. Sift flour. Stir in nuts. Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° about 1 hour or until done.

title: german chocolate cake with cream cheese filling
directions: Pour over batter.
Top with rest of batter.
Smooth.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix above ingredients into a batter.
Pour 1/2 into greased bread pan.
Layer 1 cup grated cheddar cheese and 1/4 cup chopped Italian peppers over batter.
Add rest of batter and bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes before removing.

title: super easy salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1-quart loaf pan; set aside. In medium bowl, with fork, shred salmon.
Add butter and eggs; mix until well blended.
Stir in crackers.
In small glass measuring cup, mix buttermilk with baking soda; stir in salmon mixture. Blend.
Spoon mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes until set.
Serves 4 to 5.
Very good!

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain juice off pineapple and oranges.
Mix all well together. It's better if it is made a day before you eat it.

title: top-dog hot dogs
directions: Cook hot dogs according to package directions.
Place in buns. Top with relish or chili sauce, green pepper, onion and tomato. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Yields 8 servings.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a small bowl, adding chocolate chips last.
Set aside.

title: crab triangles
directions: Mix all except crab and muffins.
Blend well.
Add crab meat; spread on English muffins.
Cut halves into quarter pie shapes. Place on cookie sheet; put in freezer until frozen.
Place in baggies.
To serve, place frozen on cookie sheet coated with Pam. 400 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crab and corn chowder soup
directions: In 3-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients.
Stir until mixed well.
Cover and place in microwave on High for 18 minutes.
Stir after 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: poor man's cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk together.
Pour on top of melted butter.
Pour fruit on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 35 minutes.
Crust will rise to top to a golden brown when done.

title: italian style rolled eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant lengthwise (leave skin on).
Dip eggplant in seasoned flour, then in beaten egg.
Fry on both sides, lay on brown paper or towels to absorb oil.
Put aside.

title: chicken and sausage casserole
directions: Use the amount of each ingredient according to your needs.

title: broccoli and carrots
directions: In pan over high heat, steam 1 pound fresh broccoli and 1/2 pound carrots, sliced.
Steam 10 minutes or until tender.
In small pan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add basil, garlic, pepper and tarragon; cook 1 minute.
Drain broccoli and carrots and pour butter mixture over vegetables.
Toss.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add the mayonnaise last.
Chill and serve.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger. Cook bacon crisp and break into small pieces. Brown onions lightly in hamburger grease.
Drain off excess fat in hamburger, bacon and onions.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: soyannaise
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients slowly.
Add oil while blending. Stir in lemon.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 pint.

title: salmon patties
directions: Remove bones and flake salmon into mixing bowl with crumbled bread and egg.
Mix together by hand.
Next, mix in flour and again knead mixture together.
Pat out into patties and fry with oil in skillet.
Makes 8 to 10, depending on size.
Serve alone or on biscuits.

title: crepes nicoise
directions: Place
the
flour, egg, egg yolk, oil, 4 tablespoons of the milk, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough milk to reduce the consistency of this cream.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Soften and dissolve unflavored gelatin in 3 tablespoons cold water.
Heat soup and add to gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into mold and chill until set.
Unmold on plate and serve with crackers.

title: bacardi golden rum cake
directions: If using yellow cake mix with pudding already in the mix, omit instant pudding and use 3 eggs instead of 4 and 1/3 cup oil instead of 1/2.

title: party squares
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and milk; boil for 2 minutes.
Take off heat and add the graham cracker crumbs, vanilla, coconut and chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Cover the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Cover crackers with filling.
Add another layer of whole graham crackers.
Press down slightly.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt.
Mix well and refrigerate mixture until stiff. Form into 1 or 2 balls or logs and roll into 2 cups chopped nuts. These may be frozen.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in corn meal.
Add eggs, milk and margarine.
Beat until smooth, but do not overbeat.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch pan or iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips and place in 8-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine.
Mix mustard, onion and 1 tablespoon margarine together. Spread mustard mixture over each chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over chicken.
Pour remaining margarine over chicken and sprinkle tarragon on top.
Cover and bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes. (Uncover the last 5 to 10 minutes.)

title: sunshine salad
directions: In large bowl, combine pie filling, whipped topping, condensed milk and lemon juice.
Reserve several mandarin orange sections. Fold remaining oranges into apricot mixture along with pineapple, marshmallows, chopped nuts and coconut.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water and debone.
Retain broth and cook noodles until tender; drain.
Add both soups and sour cream.
Mix and put in 15 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with bread cubes. Drizzle with melted margarine (on top of bread cubes).
Bake at 350° until bubbly and noodles are lightly browned (20 to 30 minutes).

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Remove bacon from pan and drain on paper towel.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add these to bacon drippings in pan. Heat thoroughly until hot.
Pour over lettuce.
Crumble bacon sprinkles over top.

title: mom's cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese and melt over medium heat; add horseradish and mayonnaise.
Mix.
Add A.1. sauce and cook a little more.
Cool. Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: bananas foster
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar in electric fry pan or chafing dish and cook over medium heat until carmelized.
Quarter bananas and cook until tender.
Add cinnamon and liqueur; stir.
Add rum or brandy to top of mixture - do not stir.
Ignite.
Spoon over ice cream while flaming.
Serves 2.

title: dessert chocolate trifle
directions: Make chocolate
cake
in
a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool. Cut into
1-inch squares.
Mix pudding with milk.
In a trifle bowl or tall clear bowl, layer chocolate cake pieces, pudding, Cool Whip and
bananas.
Repeat
layers until bowl is filled. End with
Cool Whip.
Just
before serving, slice bananas and arrange on top.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Beat softened butter, sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs together. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Stir in zucchini, chips and nuts.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco sauce together and put into pie plate.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with Doritos or tortilla chips.
Enjoy.

title: north carolina sourdough bread
directions: Combine and refrigerate covered, for 3 to 5 days. Take out and feed with starter. Do this step one time.

title: mrs. ledbetter's chocolate pie(recipes from "my just desserts")
directions: Melt chocolate and butter, stirring to blend, in top of double boiler or microwave on High, about 1 minute.
Cool slightly.
In medium bowl, beat eggs with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add sugar, cornstarch and salt; beat until smooth.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Gradually add evaporated milk and vanilla, mixing until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over filling.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until top is puffed and slightly browned.
If top browns too quickly, cover loosely with aluminum foil during last 10 minutes of baking.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the macaroni from mix until tender; drain and set aside.
In the same pan, melt butter or margarine. Blend in the flour and cheese sauce packet from dinner mix. Gradually stir in the chicken broth and beer.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add the cooked vegetables and ham.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Stir in the cooked macaroni.
If you like it not as thick, add one cup of water.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Salt and pepper cut up chicken.
Melt 1 stick butter in pan. Dip chicken in butter and put in bowl.
In another bowl, mix 1 can each: chicken, mushroom and celery soup.
Then add 1 cup rice. Put all together in baker pan and put chicken on top.
Bake at 315° for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil and beat well. Add water, then add sifted dry ingredients.
Makes 3 loaves or fill four 1 pound coffee cans 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: texas chocolate cake(makes 13 x 9-inch cake)
directions: Mix together flour and sugar, set aside.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions, but include chopped onion. Immediately add other ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles, drain.
Quickly fold in cottage cheese, sour cream and onion.
Set aside.
Cook meat.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper, garlic powder.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon half noodle mixture into well-buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with half meat mixture; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: calumet one egg cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together 3 times and set aside.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat very thoroughly.
Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased cake pans at 350° until done.
Makes 2 large layers.

title: apricot fried pies
directions: Cook diced apricots with sugar and enough water to cover apricots until tender; add cinnamon and set aside.
Make dough by cutting shortening into flour; add ice water until well mixed. Cover with plastic wrap and allow to rest for 30 minutes.

title: italian doughnuts(sfinge)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Cream eggs, sugar and butter.
Add milk and nutmeg; mix well.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat thoroughly until well blended.
Cover and set aside for 15 minutes.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry for one minute (or until golden brown).
Remove with perforated spoon. Drain.
Roll while warm in 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mix.

title: easy cookies
directions: Empty cake mix into large bowl.
Slightly beat eggs, then add eggs and oil to cake mix.
Mix well.
(Chocolate chips, nuts or raisins may be added.)
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool before serving.

title: mary perkins' pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together first 5 ingredients. Cream shortening. Gradually blend in sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating about 1 minute after each.
Blend in pumpkin.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Combine egg and meat.
Mix other ingredients with scalded milk.
Let stand 10 minutes until cracker crumbs swell and form a thick mixture.
Add to the meat and egg mixture.
Press into loaf; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in Italian dressing, 24 to 48 hours. Cook the chicken breasts on the grill.
Slice the cooked chicken in strips.
Place chicken strips in a flour tortilla.
Add sour cream, guacamole, cheese, lettuce and olives to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fudge brownie cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in heavy pan.
Add nuts and cool. Combine sugar and flour.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture.
Mix well.
Do not beat.
Bake in foil-lined cupcake tins at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on box.
While hot, add marshmallows and cream cheese.
Set aside to cool.
Add pineapple, whipped cream (or Dream Whip) and nuts.
Cream together and chill.

title: corn and zucchini
directions: Place zucchini in pan with water and salt, cover. Boil until tender, about 10 minutes, drain. Chop zucchini when cool enough to handle. Melt 3 Tbsp. butter in skillet. Add onion, garlic and green pepper, saut until soft. Stir in zucchini, remaining butter, cheese, eggs, and corn, mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Melt margarine; add remaining pie ingredients in order listed. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon cheese salad(congealed)
directions: Boil 1 cup water and dissolve jello.
Measure drained pineapple juice and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add this to the jello and chill until partially set.
Soften cream cheese and mix with mayonnaise.
Add this mixture to partially
set jello and stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold or container and chill.

title: brownie torte
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels and butter over hot (not boiling) water; heat until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Pour into a large bowl. Mix in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually blend in flour. Stir in nuts.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.

title: herbal animal bath
directions: This herbal bath is an excellent way to rid your animals of fleas without using harsh chemical soaps or powders.

title: j.w.'s surprise(cabbage casserole)
directions: Steam/boil cabbage 5 minutes.
Add onion and steam/boil 2 minutes.
Drain and place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add soup and cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Place in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: zesty barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring constantly for 15 minutes.

title: lemon blue cheese dressing
directions: Mash cheese until creamy.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Serve on wedges of head lettuce.
May be thinned, if desired, with cream, sour cream or mayonnaise.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Slowly pour chocolate over mixture and stir to evenly coat.
Spread mixture on waxed paper and cool.
Break into small pieces.
Store in an airtight container and refrigerate to keep fresh.

title: congealed salad(preparation time: 15 minutes)
directions: Mix all the ingredients well; put into covered dish and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding mix.
Beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Layer in 2 1/2 to 3-quart glass serving bowl.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells by directions on box.
Drain and place shells in large baking pan.
Brown ground meat.
Add egg, onion, seasoning, garlic, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Heat until well blended.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Pour Ragu sauce over shells and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, brown sugar, cooking oil, vanilla and eggs.
Mix together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Fold in. Add cornflakes, nuts, chocolate chips, oatmeal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini chocolate bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar together.
Add the zucchini and vanilla.
Combine the flour, cocoa, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder, and add to the zucchini mixture.
Add the nuts. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 325° for 45-60 minutes, or until bread tests done.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sherbet and mix well. When partially set, add mandarin oranges and fold in Cool Whip. Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: billy's casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease (Pam) a square baking dish.
Spread broccoli in dish.
Beat together sour cream, cottage cheese, Bisquick, margarine and eggs with hand beater for 1 minute.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake until brown on top, about 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and form well in middle of mixture.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla and pour into dry ingredients.
Stir until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Add apples, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° in a Bundt pan for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stick knife in center of cake to check for doneness.

title: broccoli casserole 4
directions: Mix together well and bake for 1 hour.

title: mexican madness
directions: Fry ground beef with taco seasoning per package directions. In 8 x 10-inch baking dish, spread beans.
Top with meat. Sprinkle with cheese and top with taco sauce.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with olives and chilies.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash and onion in boiling water until tender, then drain.
Add cracker crumbs, butter, 1 cup cheese, salt and pepper. Beat eggs lightly and add milk. Mix with squash mixture.
Pour into a buttered casserole and sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 425° until done.
About 8 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 12 cup muffin tin with margarine. Combine whole wheat flour, wheat bran, brown sugar, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, mix buttermilk, egg, molasses and oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix until just moistened.
Fold in raisins.
Fill muffin tin and bake for about 15 minutes.
Per muffin:
116 total calories and 4 sat fat.

title: pumpkin or squash pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Then add the rest.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for about 10 minutes, then reduce heat to moderate 325° about 40 minutes or until filling is firm.
Serve plain or with sweetened whipped cream.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine and cream cheese well.
Add sugar, cream well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add all of the flavorings.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and add glaze.

title: orval's spaghetti(from his kindergarten recipe)
directions: You slice 8 apples and you put them in a pan.
Put chocolate kethup over them.
Then you cook them.
I don't know how long.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Break crackers into single; line long shallow pan.
One box does 2 batches (recommend Keebler).
Melt together margarine and sugar.
Heat to boiling and boil slowly for 3 minutes; stir constantly.
Pour over crackers and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool and break apart.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix and stir with fork until soft dough is formed.
Beat until stiff; turn out on board lightly dusted with flour.
Knead gently; roll to 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Cut dough in half lengthwise, then cut each half crosswise into 16 strips.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan in oven.
Dip each strip in the melted butter, turning to coat both sides.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 12 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 32 bread sticks.

title: busy-day chicken pie
directions: Rinse chicken.
Cook in water to cover in saucepan until tender.
Bone and chop chicken; reserve 1 1/2 cups chicken broth. Combine chicken, reserved broth, eggs and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Combine flour and milk in small bowl; mix to form dough. Roll on floured surface to fit 3-quart baking dish.
Place in dish.
Dot with butter.
Spoon chicken mixture into pastry.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil cans; cover completely with water (or will explode) for 3 hours.
Cool.
Mix caramel, mini chocolate chips and chopped pecans.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with mini chocolate chips.
Refrigerate.

title: dirt
directions: Combine oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Add vanilla pudding and milk; beat at low speed until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Crush Oreos in food processor or blender. Alternate layers of Oreos and pudding, starting and finishing with Oreos.
It's really cute if you put it in a flower pot and decorate with silk flowers and gummy worms.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and spice.
Add persimmon pulp, mashed sweet potato, milk, eggs, melted margarine and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve hot or cold, with whipped cream or plain.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix with hands.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields about 100 cocktail-size balls.
Serve hot. May be frozen before baking.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Roll each piece of biscuits in sugar and cinnamon.
Grease bundt pan and put a layer of biscuit pieces in the bottom.
Sprinkle pecan pieces over first layer and add another layer of biscuits.
Boil butter and brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Remove at once and serve hot.

title: granny's sweet bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well. Pour into a heavy skillet that has been well-greased, floured and heated. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Make layer of lettuce, cheese, onion and peas.
Sprinkle each layer with salt, pepper, sugar and 3 teaspoons Miracle Whip. Repeat so you will have three layers.
Let stand 4 hours or overnight.
Crumble bacon on top before serving.

title: barbecue chicken(coca-cola style)
directions: Brown chicken in butter; drain.
Mix catsup, Coca-Cola and onion.
Pour over chicken and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: corn dip
directions: Put butter and cream cheese in
microwave. Cook on Medium until butter melts.

Beat until smooth (will appear curdled). Drain corn (reserving juice) and add to cream cheese mixture. Add peppers and cumin to taste. Stir in corn juice to desired consistency, being careful not to get too runny. Serve warm.
A chafing dish is perfect.

title: terrific cornbread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients. Beat the egg with milk and add it to the flour mixture, along with melted butter. Stir; mix well. Spread batter in a buttered 9-inch baking dish. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cornbread is lightly browned around the edges.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: In medium saucepan, whisk salad dressing and milk over low heat until smooth.
Add cheese, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat 1 or 2 minutes until thick and smooth.
Toss with noodles; serve immediately.

title: country casserole breakfast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Line bottom of casserole with bread.
Add sausage.
Mix eggs, cheese, milk, salt, pepper and mustard; pour over bread and sausage.
Refrigerate overnight (important).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until brown. Serves 8 to 12.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with veggies or chips.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Cook small head of cabbage until tender.
Stir mayonnaise and salt into cabbage and pour into casserole dish.
Layer with ground beef.
Mix 1/2 can water or milk to mushroom soup and mix well.
Then pour this over ground beef.
Place grated cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: molasses snaps
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients, then add dry ingredients. Roll dough into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten into circles with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then chocolate and liquids and stir until smooth.
Add chocolate last, makes a rich color.
Bake in pan (11 x 7-inch) in 350° oven.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Blanch carrots until crisp, about 6 to 8 minutes and drain. Add green pepper and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots, green pepper and onion, mix and chill.
Will keep 10 days.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Chop beef into squares (I use my little Oscar).
Mix 1/2 beef with ingredients and form ball (it's messy).
I put mixture on a piece of Saran Wrap and mold with plastic instead of hands.
Roll ball in remaining beef (or make a second ball with meat and roll ball in pecans).
Chill.
Best when made 1 to 2 days in advance. Flavor seeps through cream cheese.

title: crab and pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain; add all of the other ingredients.
Coat with 2 bottles of Good Seasons Italian dressing.
Chill overnight.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes; mash well.
Add the sour cream, cream cheese, onion salt and garlic salt; mix well.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Put in refrigerator; let set overnight.
Before baking, dot with butter (do not stir).
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover; let top brown slightly.

title: date balls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, eggs and dates in pan.
Bring to a boil and
cook
minutes.
Remove
from
heat, add nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Shape in balls and roll in coconut.

title: beef soup with noodles
directions: Wash meat and bones.
Let soak in enough water to cover them until some of blood is washed off.
Put meat and bones in large pot.
Add cold water enough to cover.
Cook until foam gathers on top on medium heat.
Scoop foam out with strainer.
Cover until boils.
Lower heat and cook 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Add rest of ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 25 to 30 minutes. Do not boil again.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Slice and dice rhubarb; add a little water and soak.
Mash, then add sugar.
Add strawberries, cinnamon and jello.
This makes a sauce with the consistency of applesauce.

title: scripture cake
directions: Look in the Bible for the chapter and verse.
Follow Solomon's advice for making boys good and you will have a good cake. Proverbs 23:14.
Proceed with ordinary rules for cake mixing.
Add nuts last.
Bake in tube or loaf pan at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pancakes
directions: Have all ingredients room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour onto slightly greased preheated pan.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Saute onion and green pepper in drippings.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together in ovenproof casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly (about 20 to 30 minutes).

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into Bundt pan or makes 18 to 24 muffins.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: sue's chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Frost with whipped topping or eat plain.

title: chocolate raspberry pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12 cup fluted tube pan. Melt 3/4 cup of the preserves; cool.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add butter, sour cream, eggs, vanilla and melted preserves.
Beat on medium speed 3 or 4 minutes until well blended.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan to wire rack. Melt remaining 1/4 cup of preserves.
Brush over warm cake.
Cool completely.
At serving time, sprinkle powdered sugar over top. Garnish as desired.
Fill the middle of the cake (cavity) with Raspberry Cream recipe .
(Red raspberry preserves may be substituted).

title: bread
directions: Put yeast, sugar, milk powder and 3 cups flour into large bowl.
Add warm water and stir.
Add oil and beat well for 2 minutes with wooden spoon.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour.
Mix until the dough comes off the sides of bowl.
Place the dough on lightly floured board and knead 6 to 9 minutes.
If dough is sticky, sprinkle with flour.
Shape into ball and place in lightly greased bowl.
Rotate dough so all sides are greased.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel.
Let rise in warm place 60 to 90 minutes.

title: peanut butter supremes
directions: Blend shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar and brown sugar; mix well.
Beat in eggs until fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Stir in peanut butter mixture.
Mix well.
Shape dough into small balls.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble the 3 breads together in large pan.
Add eggs, sage, salt, pepper, onion, celery and melted butter.
Mix in together the chicken broth, water and milk.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix together. Will be thin.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.
May be poured into several pans.
Can freeze what you don't use.

title: mike's vegetable and rice fry
directions: Place rice in a skillet with margarine or oil.
Cook on medium-high
heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to rice.
Cook until vegetables are tender but make sure rice doesn't get mushy.

title: deviled crab
directions: Mix in bowl the raw egg, vinegar and seasonings.
Add diced eggs, crab meat and melted butter.
Put mixture into empty crab shells or a dish.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° or 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes 4 servings or may be made into small balls and served as an appetizer.

title: crab and wild rice
directions: Cook rice, saute mushrooms in butter, stir in soup and cream. Mix until smooth.
In 2-quart greased casserole, layer 1/2 rice, soup and cheese. Repeat. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Beat in sugar; stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour and spices.
Fold into pumpkin.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Top with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll towel and cake together.
Cool.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion together.
Drain well and add taco seasoning.
On a platter:
First Layer, refried beans. Second Layer, beef mixture.
Third Layer, olives and diced tomatoes.
Fourth Layer, chopped lettuce.
Cover with sour cream and shredded cheese of your choice.
Dip taco chips in it or spread on chips with a knife.
Serve with salsa on the side.

title: cocoa cream pie
directions: Scald milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir some of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Blend egg yolk mixture into hot mixture.
Return to stove and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add butter and vanilla. Pour immediately into baked pie shell.
Spread with meringue, sealing to edge of crust to prevent shrinking.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until a delicate brown.
Let cool at room temperature.

title: homestyle baked beans
directions: Brown onion, pepper and beef, then drain.
Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: alfredo pasta
directions: Melt the butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Add the cream, garlic powder and pepper and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes or until thick. At the same time, bring 4 to 6 quarts of water to a boil and add the pasta. When the alfredo sauce has reached your desired consistency, stir in the Parmesan cheese. When the pasta is cooked, drain it. Serve the pasta on plates with alfredo sauce poured over the top. Serves 2 to 3 as an entree.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Scramble sausage; pour in casserole dish.
Then add both soups, cheese, onion, rice and water.
Mix together and then top with crackers and butter.
Bake until it starts to bubble, then serve.

title: peppered beef with rice
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Add onion and steak strips and brown about 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. Cover and reduce heat to low. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Bring to a boil margarine, cocoa, vanilla, milk and powdered sugar (gradually).
(Use more or less sugar, depending on desired consistency.)
Keep cake refrigerated.

title: strawberry pie i
directions: Mash 1 cup berries; add rest of ingredients and let come to a boil.
Take off stove and beat well.
Cool thoroughly.
Pour cooked mixture into baked pie shell over whole strawberries. Serve cold.
May garnish with Cool Whip if desired.

title: daria's delight(sweet potato pie)
directions: Boil potatoes.
Once done, using very clean hands or hands covered with disposable gloves, squish the cooled potatoes into a complete mess!
Now add the sugar to taste, adding a little more or a little less.
Now add butter (melted) and all other items and stir using large potato spoon.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add cream of mushroom soup. Add cheese and olives.
Add chicken to other ingredients.
Then add to cooked spaghetti.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour; saute in butter until brown.
Mix soup, onion and seasonings in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour rice right from box into a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Stir all except 1/3 cup of soup mixture over rice.
Top with chicken.
Pour rest of soup mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Cook sausages. Combine apricot preserves and mustard in saucepan and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Add sausages and simmer 15 minutes longer. Serve hot from chafing dish, electric frying pan or buffet warmer.
Spear with picks to eat.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Add chopped celery and add enough mayonnaise to make moist.

title: toffee
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in thick saucepan.
Cook on medium-low heat.
Use a candy thermometer.
Stir constantly until it reaches 300°.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour quickly into ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Allow to stand 2 minutes.
Spread chocolate chips evenly over toffee and sprinkle nuts on top.
Allow to harden.
Break in pieces and serve.

title: rice krispie peanut butter treats
directions: Mix together first three ingredients; bring to a boil for one minute, then add 2 cups peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir together until it melts.
Add box of Rice Krispies, then roll into balls.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place chicken in bottom of long dish.
Sprinkle garlic salt and red pepper.
Slice cheese on top and 1/2 bag crushed chips. Mix soups and Ro-Tel in blender.
Pour on top.
Slightly put rest of crushed chips on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes more.

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Best if chilled overnight.
Good served with any kind of whole wheat crackers.

title: "puppy chow" for people
directions: Melt oleo, chocolate chips and peanut butter in Dutch oven. Remove from heat and stir in cereal until well coated (stir gently please).
Place powdered sugar in a large brown paper grocery bag and add chocolate/cereal mixture.
Shake until well coated; it takes several minutes to thoroughly coat.
I serve in a dog dish (new clean one)!

title: fresh blueberry crunch
directions: Place blueberries in a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fluffy pecan dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat whites until soft peaks form. Add sugar, baking powder and salt. Beat until sugar is dissolved and meringue is stiff. Stir in vanilla, pecans and cereal crumbs. Spread filling evenly on greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake for 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Top with whipped cream. Sprinkle with additional chopped pecans.

title: healthy apple cobbler
directions: Layer oats in bottom of 8-inch square nonstick pan.
Add apple slices.
Combine apple juice, cinnamon and cloves; pour over apples and oats.
Sprinkle raisins on top.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil; cover with crunchy cereal and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chow-chow
directions: Grind all vegetables and drain juice off. Add a quart or more if needed, of white vinegar. Add all remaining ingredients, mix well and cook for 30 minutes. Fill hot jars and seal. Boil sealed jars in water for 10 minutes. Makes 8 pints.

title: sugar muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in muffin tin at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: dilled zucchini pickles
directions: Mix zucchini, celery, onions and salt.
Place a layer of ice on top.
Cover and let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Combine sugar, dill seed and vinegar and heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Stir in vegetables and heat to a rolling boil, stirring several times.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars.
Put 1 or 2 pieces of garlic in each jar and seal.

title: smoked bass fillet
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour liquid smoke into shallow dish. Dip fillets in liquid smoke, soaking both sides.
Place fillets in shallow baking pan, making sure fillets are not touching.
Sprinkle prime rib rub on fillets and place in oven.
After allowing it to bake 5 to 7 minutes, lightly brush melted butter on each fillet. Bake until they flake easily, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Saute carrots and onion in margarine.
Add soup and sour cream.
Add cooked and drained zucchini.
Add croutons.
Toss lightly to mix.
Bake in covered casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the oleo, or butter and oleo, and sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until edges are slightly browned.
(I put teaspoon of batter and "smash" with glass dipped in sugar.)

title: zesty chicken
directions: Place chicken breast in baking pan; mix barbecue sauce, brown sugar and drained juice from pineapples.
Pour chicken and spread pineapple chunks over chicken.
Bake until chicken is done.

title: window cleaner
directions: Mix preceding in a gallon milk jug that has been rinsed out. Fill with water.
Use to fill spray bottle.

title: rattlesnake stew(not really)
directions: Mix meat and onion and cook; drain well.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, corn, peas and mushrooms, juice and all.
Add 2 tomato sauce cans full of water; stir well and add macaroni.
Cook, covered, on low until macaroni is tender.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat, garlic and onion.
Add tomatoes, salt, oregano powder, pepper and sauce.
Cook in skillet 1/2 hour.
Boil noodles 15 minutes in 3 quarts salted water.
In greased casserole dish layer noodles, American cheese, cottage cheese and hamburger mixture until all gone.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine the last 4 ingredients.
Pour this over the top of the corn and green beans which have been put in a buttered casserole (9 x 13-inch dish).
Take 1 package of crushed Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Melt 1 stick oleo and pour over topping.
Bake in a 350° oven until onions are tender, about 45 minutes.

title: 9-day slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and mustard seed and bring to a boil.
Add vegetables; stir and let chill.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: This recipe is traditionally for using up leftover vegetables; however, if you don't happen to have them, it is worth starting from scratch.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Spoon 1 1/2-quarts of sherbet into punch bowl. Let soften at room temperature for 5 minutes. Then slowly pour in chilled 7-Up, stirring slightly in order to combine with sherbet.
Float generous scoopfuls of remaining sherbet on top of punch.
Makes about 50 punch cup servings.

title: cranberry fizz
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 16 1/2-cup servings.

title: eggs newport
directions: Using 1 1/2-quart dish, layer sliced eggs, cheese, bacon and sauce.
Continue but reserve enough bacon to sprinkle over top. Start with the eggs.
Serve over English muffins or toast points. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make into loaf.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: Mix chop meat, eggs and onion soup together.
Let mixture set for a while or overnight in the refrigerator.
Roll in small meatballs, then bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until brown.
Meanwhile, bring puree and cranberry sauce to a slow boil. Drain meatballs.
Add to heated sauce and cover.
Simmer for 5 or 6 hours in slow cooker or electric frying pan or cook in an oven set on low.
Check and stir meatballs occasionally so they don't stick to pan.
Makes about 30 meatballs.
Serve alone or over noodles or rice or Italian bread.

title: pear salad
directions: Open pears; drain juice.
Put a spoonful of mayo in center of pear.
Top with cheese.
Place cherry on top and arrange on platter of lettuce.

title: layered salad
directions: For the first layer, mix all ingredients except the cheese, eggs and bacon.
Mix the mayo and sugar and frost the vegetables with the mixture.
For the second layer, mix cheese and bacon and top all with slices of eggs.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shread cabbage and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess fluid.

title: ginger creams
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, ginger, nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Cream the butter and gradually add sugar. Blend in egg.
Mix well.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the molasses and hot water.
Blend thoroughly after each addition. Chill dough 30 to 60 minutes.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 9 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute and remove from sheet.
Frost with buttercream frosting.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: oriental wing n dings
directions: Cut off chicken wing tips at joint.
Discard tips or save for making chicken broth.
Cut each remaining wing portion at other joint to make 2 pieces.
Place in large plastic bag.
Combine 1/4 cup soy sauce, sherry, garlic and brown sugar in cup; pour over chicken wings.
Close bag securely; turn to coat.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 4 hours or up to 24 hours.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sesame oil and remaining 2 teaspoons soy sauce in small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Drain chicken wings or dings; reserve marinade.
Place wings or dings on rack of broiler pan.
Brush with half of reserved marinade.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 10 minutes.
Turn wings and brush with remaining marinade.
Broil 10 minutes until chicken is browned and cooked through.
Use mayonnaise mixture as a dipping sauce for wings.
Makes 2 dozen appetizers.

title: goulash and salad
directions: Brown ground meat and add okra, cook until tender.
Add corn, sausage or wieners.
Cook about 3 minutes and then add tomato sauce; cook for 5 minutes.
Add cooked rice.
You will have a full meal.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening to texture of corn meal; then add milk and vinegar.
Roll out and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
