Any leftover dough will keep in refrigerator for weeks in a closed container.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° until set in middle about 30 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Let butter melt in a 3-quart saucepan until softened, but not running.
Then add sugar and boil until 1 tablespoon of mixture will harden in cold water.
Do not allow to turn dark in color. Pour over chopped nuts to cool.

title: wonderful hamburger casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; drain, season and mash; set aside.
Chop and slightly cook onion in skillet; add hamburger.
Cook and drain. Add drained green beans.
Add tomato soup.
Mix together salt and pepper to taste.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Add mashed potatoes in serving size with ice cream dipper.
Put in 350° oven until potatoes are slightly brown.

title: rack of lamb
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place lamb on a rack in a greased large baking pan, brush with mustard.
In a small bowl, combine the bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Press onto the meat. Combine butter and garlic, drizzle over meat.
Bake for 30-40 minutes or until meat reaches desired doneness (160 degrees for medium-well, 170 degrees for well-done).
Yield:
8 servings.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine and baking soda together.
Measure molasses; put soda into cup and add boiling water.
Hold cup over pie shell when adding water, as it will bubble over.
Crumble crumb mixture into liquid in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Finished pie should have a gooey layer on bottom and dry crumbs on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
No milk or baking powder needed.
Bake in loaf pan 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add 2 eggs, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Alternate flour mixture with milk.
Stir in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Spread half of the chocolate mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then spread the cream cheese mixture.
Spread the balance of chocolate mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate almond bark
directions: Combine over hot (not boiling) water, Nestle Toll House milk chocolate morsels and vegetable shortening.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in raisins and 1/4 cup almonds.
Spread into wax-paper lined 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining almonds on top.
Chill until ready to serve (about 30 minutes before serving); break into bite size pieces.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix
first
ingredients by hand and roll into 1-inch balls. Melt
chocolate
and paraffin in top of double boiler. Add vanilla.
Using toothpicks, dip balls in chocolate mixture and place on wax paper to dry.

title: roast beef mold
directions: Mix together and pour into a mold of your choice.

title: mandarin salad
directions: In a small saucepan over medium heat, cook almonds and sugar, stirring constantly until almonds are coated and sugar is dissolved (be careful, they will burn easily).
Cool.
Store in air tight container.
In a small bowl, mix together the salt, pepper, parsley, sugar, vinegar and tabasco sauce for the dressing.
Set aside.
Mix lettuce, celery and onions.
Just before serving, add almonds and oranges.
Toss with dressing.
Serves 4-6.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream oleo and eggs (one at a time).
Add flour, sugar, vanilla and milk.
Mix together and add rest of the ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Glaze or ice.

title: miniature cheese loaves
directions: Mix together lightly all ingredients except cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Shape in 8 small meat loaves and place on a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Press cheese cubes into each loaf; cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until brown.
Cool and refrigerate.
To serve, heat in spaghetti sauce until well heated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer for at least 3 hours.

title: prime rib
directions: Rub meat down with garlic.
Mix broth and both sauces in large pan.
Place meat in juice; marinate for 1/2 hour.
Save juice. Place meat in a pan with a rack so juice can drip off meat.
Put in oven at 450° for 1/2 hour.
Turn oven to 350°.
Baste with juice mixture every 1/2 hour.
Do not cover meat.
Cook 1/2 hour for every pound for a medium roast.

title: jello balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Roll in small balls and refrigerate overnight.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together just before serving.
Chill with floating ice ring.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour crust over chicken mixture.

title: christmas rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Stir twice while cooking.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and top with cheese.
Combine soup and wine.
Spoon over chicken and sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes, uncovered.

title: mixed bean salad
directions: Drain
canned beans well.
Add peppers; combine remaining ingredients
and
mix well.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours before using.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in egg. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in Raisinets, oats and nuts. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to stand 2 minutes before removing.
Cool completely.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: suzy's rice pudding
directions: Stir cornstarch and sugar in cold milk.
Heat the mixture until it boils.
Add rice.
Stir continuously until the pudding thickens and the rice is done.
Pour in small bowls.
Let it cool, then refrigerate.
Garnish with pistachio, then serve.

title: chocolate reese balls
directions: Melt paraffin and chips in double boiler and keep hot while dipping balls into it.
Lay on waxed paper.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until softly fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon juice and vanilla.
Pour in prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours, until set.
Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into buttered baking dish.
Mix with fork until crumbly all remaining ingredients.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with powdered sugar. Optional, but great topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken breasts with garlic sauce
directions: Brown chicken breasts in skillet sprayed with Pam.
In small bowl, mix sugar, wine vinegar, garlic and chicken broth. Gradually add cornstarch and mix thoroughly. Add sliced onion and bell peppers in skillet with chicken breasts.
Pour liquid mixture over top of onion and peppers.
Simmer about 15 or 20 minutes or until tender.
Add seasonings to taste. Serve alone or over rice. Makes 2 servings.
Each serving has 2 fat grams.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and shape into balls. Place in casserole dish. Mix the rest of the ingredients together and pour over meatballs. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Measure first, then pulverize in blender until all turns to powder; put small amounts in blender.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a double boiler over boiling water, stirring until the cheeses are melted and blended well with the spices and chilies.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; cut in softened butter.
Add other ingredients and mix.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, add oil, sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Add zucchini; mix flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Add coconut, nuts and raisins, if desired. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix salad dressing.
Add 6 teaspoons sugar and enough milk to thin salad dressing.
Pour over ingredients and mix.

title: microwave vanilla pudding
directions: Combine cornstarch and sugar in 2-quart microwave safe mixing bowl.
Using a whisk, add milk gradually to cornstarch and sugar mix.
Place mixture in microwave.
Microwave on high for 5 to 7 minutes or until bubbly and thick, stirring after 2 minute intervals.
Beat 1/2 of the hot mixture into the slightly beaten eggs.

Beat this mixture into the remaining hot mixture. Microwave on high for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes until thickened and heated throughout, stirring after every 45 seconds of cooking. With whisk, stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour mixture in equal amounts into 4 dishes.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place ham fat side up on rack in open roasting pan; sprinkle with ground cloves.
Bake tenderized ham about 25 minutes to the pound.
If it is the ready to eat variety, bake only 10 to 12 minutes to the pound.
Thirty minutes before baking time is up, baste the ham every 5 to 10 minutes with desired glaze.
Serves 10.

title: glazed cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until very warm (120°).
Combine 2 cups flour and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Gradually add milk mixture to flour mixture, stirring well.
Add egg.
Beat medium speed until smooth. Gradually stir in enough flour to make a slightly stiff dough.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Gently pull off 8 large cabbage leaves from the head.
Simmer in 1-inch boiling water, covered, for 5 minutes.
Drain and lay out for filling.

title: pineapple-cheese mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into a 1-quart bowl.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cider waldorf mold
directions: In a saucepan, bring 1 c. apple cider or juice to a boil; add jell-o and stir until dissolved.
Stir in remaining cider or juice; chill until partially set.
Fold in apple, celery and pecans.
Pour into a 3 c. mold or spoon into 6 individual molds. Chill until firm.
Unmold salad on lettuce-lined plates.
Serve with mayonnaise or salad dressing.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese (chopped in small pieces), milk and pimento (which should be mashed fine before adding) over low heat, stirring all the time.
As soon as cheese melts, remove from heat.
Cool and add enough mayonnaise to spread easily.

title: cocktail rye bread cheesios
directions: Chop onion fine.
Shred cheese.
Mix onion and cheese together.
Add mayo and Lea & Perrins until spreadable.
Spread on bread.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes, until golden brown.
These cook easy and quick so keep an eye on them.

title: cold slaw dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix in eggs and seasonings.
Mix in oats and nuts.
Stir in flour.
Bake at 350°.

title: miso soup
directions: Boil the shrimp, dried mushrooms and konbu in water for about 1/2 hour.
Add vegetables and simmer until tender.
Add about 2 heaping tablespoons miso paste.
Garnish with tofu and green onions or other optional ingredients.

title: sicilian supper
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings; simmer 5 minutes.
Saute green pepper in margarine; add cream cheese and milk, stirring until cream cheese melts.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, salt and noodles. In a 6 x 10-inch baking dish, arrange alternate crosswise rows of meat and noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream cheese braids
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar, butter and salt in saucepan; heat until butter melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream mixture and eggs.
Gradually stir in flour.
Dough will be soft. Cover dough tightly and chill at least 8 hours.
Divide dough into 4 equal portions.
Turn each portion onto a heavily floured surface and knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll each portion into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle; spread with filling, leaving a 1/2-inch margin around edges.
Carefully roll up dough jelly roll fashion, starting at long side.
Pinch the seam and ends to seal.
Carefully place loaves, seam side down, on greased baking sheets.
Make 6 equally spaced X-shaped cuts across top of each loaf.
Cover and let rise in warm place (85°), free from drafts, about 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread loaves with glaze while warm.
Yields four 12-inch loaves.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir well and chill several hours.
Serves 8.

title: tangy broccoli salad
directions: Mix dressing, sugar and vinegar in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving. Serves:

title: pound cake
directions: Fill powdered sugar box with cake flour; adding small amounts at a time to mixture.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Flavor to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: charlotte's chicken soup
directions: Pat chicken parts dry. Season with salt and pepper. Brown chicken in heavy Dutch oven with 1 teaspoon canola oil over medium-high heat for about 6 to 8 minutes, turning once. Add chicken broth and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover partially and simmer until chicken is cooked through, about 20 minutes. Using tongs, transfer chicken to large bowl. Cool chicken. Debone and cut into bite size pieces. Spoon fat off broth. Return broth to simmer. Add onion, carrots, celery and thyme. Simmer until vegetables are softened, about 8 minutes. (Can be prepared one day ahead, but be sure to store broth and meat separately in fridge.) Stir in noodles, parsley and chicken. Simmer until noodles are tender, about 5 minutes. If using rice, simmer until rice is done. Season soup to taste with salt and pepper.

title: impossible garden pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle first 4 ingredients in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer).
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 35 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes and garnish with tomato and zucchini slices.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle one side of beef steak with half of the flour mixture; pound in.
Turn beef and pound in remaining flour mixture.
Cut beef into 6 serving pieces.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet until hot.
Cook beef in oil over medium heat, turning once, until brown, about 10 minutes.
Add onion.
Mix remaining ingredients except water and mushrooms; stir in water and mushrooms.
Pour over beef.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings; 180 calories per serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil, cool and chop chicken into small portions.
Mix cream of celery soup in with chopped chicken.
Place in casserole dish. Pour cream of mushroom soup over this, spreading evenly.
Simmer on stove the butter and chicken broth; let cool.
Stir in Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Spread over chicken and soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pineapple pie
directions: Add lemon juice to Eagle Brand milk in a medium bowl.
Fold in remaining ingredients and pour into baked pie crust.
So good and easy.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: In a large baking dish, put one layer of meat, then a layer of potatoes.
Last layer is onions.
After mixing all the soups together with only enough water to wash each can, pour soup mixture over your layers of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until meat is brown and potatoes are tender.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos and set aside.
Make pudding with milk and set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Add to pudding. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer pudding and Oreo's, ending with Oreo's.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Cook seasonings in butter and add seafood.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Add soups.
Cut up cheese in cubes and add to mixture. Cook until cheese melts.
Boil noodles and drain.
Mix noodles and sauce just before serving.
Serve hot.

title: cioppino(pronounced chee-o-pee-no - italian seafood stew)
directions: In a large saucepan, cook green pepper, onion and garlic in olive oil until tender, but not brown.
Add undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, wine, parsley, salt, oregano, basil and pepper; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine.
Add sugar and beat.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Add other ingredients except egg whites and beat. Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked spinach dip
directions: Mix and place in hollowed bread bowl wrapped in foil or casserole. Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh tomato spaghetti(for summer enjoyment)
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 3 hours before using.
Mix into hot cooked spaghetti and serve.
It cools quickly so be ready to eat as soon as served.
Especially nice with garden home grown tomatoes.

title: no-bake peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, half and half, vanilla and peanut butter together until smooth. In a small glass bowl, whip heavy cream until stiff. Add the whipped cream to peanut butter mixture and fold in. Spoon into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate 1 hour or until served.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Grease a 12-cup Bundt pan. In a large mixing bowl, mix the cake mix, oil, water and eggs together with an electric mixer on low speed until the ingredients are well distributed, about 1 minute. Scrape the bottom of the bowl with a spatula and beat for 2 minutes, still on low speed. Add the container of frosting and continue beating on low speed for about 2 minutes. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake until a cake tester inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes. Let the cake cool in the pan. Invert the cooled cake onto a plate and allow it to cool thoroughly before slicing. No frosting is needed, it's already in the cake.

title: unbelieveable peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat the egg slightly in a bowl.
Add the sugar, peanut butter and vanilla and beat together until smooth. Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 20 minutes or until nicely brown.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: herbed new potatoes
directions: Peel 1/2 inch strip around the center of each potato and immediately place potatoes in a medium saucepan of cold water. Cover with water and bring to a boil until potatoes are easily pierced by a fork but firm, about 20 minutes; drain.
Cover to keep warm.
Place the butter in a microwave safe bowl and heat on HIGH until melted, 5-10 seconds.
Stir in parsley and chives.
Pour this mixture over the potatoes and toss to coat.
Pour into serving bowl, garnish and serve immediately.
For variety, can be sprinkled with chopped cooked bacon or finely minced green onions.

title: martha washington candy
directions: You will need wax paper and toothpicks.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Next mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour into dish with margarine. Add chopped fruit.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 more minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar and serve hot with ice cream.

title: carrot bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs until well blended.
In another bowl, sift flour with salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Add this to first mixture and blend well, then add the jars of baby food.
Fill two greased and floured loaf pans, each 2/3 full. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible quiche tarts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 18 muffin cups.

title: microwave risotto
directions: Heat oil 2 minutes in deep microwave dish; stir in onion. Cook 4 minutes.
Stir in rice; cook 4 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth; cook 9 minutes. Cook after stirring 9 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes. If rice is not completely absorbed, cook 5 minutes more. Add cheese.

title: sparkly's surprise punch
directions: Chill pineapple juice and 7-Up.
Pour additional 7-Up into 2 ice cube trays, placing a maraschino cherry in each cube. Freeze.
At serving time, combine pineapple juice and concentrated orange juice in punch bowl.
Add peppermint extract for a little added snap, if desired.
Slowly pour in chilled 7-Up.
Add decorated 7-Up "ice" cubes.
Makes about 30 servings.

title: lemon tarts
directions: Combine eggs, 8 egg yolks, 1 cup sugar, lemon rind, and lemon juice in a medium bowl; beat at high speed of an electric mixer until thick and lemon colored. Transfer egg mixture to top of double boiler. Cook over simmering water, stirring constantly with wire whisk, 10 to 15 minutes or until egg mixture is thickened.

title: cookie crust
directions: Mix together oleo and sugar; do not cream.
Mix in flour.
Pat in crust.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix sugar in milk in top of 2-quart double boiler.
Heat about to boiling point.
Stir eggs in.
Cook until mixture coats a spoon.
Do not boil.

title: italian bread(great as an appetizer or to accompany meal)
directions: Grate cheeses.
Mix with other ingredients.
Slice French loaf lengthwise.
Spread mixture on bread, covering to edges.
Place on cookie sheet under broiler until bubbly.
Slice into 1 1/2-inch pieces to serve.

title: one, two, three, four cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt slowly into mixture.
Add milk and vanilla; beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Bake in medium oven.

title: olive dreams(appetizer)
directions: Cut muffins into fourths.
Mix all ingredients and spread each muffin piece with a generous dollop of cheese mixture.
Broil until bubbly.

title: lemon chess bars
directions: Mix together in mixer; dough will be stiff.
Press in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, then add topping.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat and garlic in skillet. Drain fat. In mixing bowl, blend next 4 ingredients; stir in meat. Prepare manicotti noodles according to package directions.

Fill each noodle with cheese and meat mixture and place in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with any remaining filling and cover with spaghetti sauce. Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese and cover pan with foil. Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes. Remove foil and bake 10 minutes more. Serve 4 to 6.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Combine berries, sugar and lemon juice in a 6-quart aluminum cooker.
Place over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook for 15 minutes on high or at a temperature at which preserves can't be stirred down.
Cool and ladle into jars.
Preserves freeze well, too.

title: hot tuna 'n toast
directions: Melt butter
in
saucepan.
Slowly
stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk a little at a time until blended.
Cook over low heat, stirring
until thickened.
Add peas, tuna, salt and pepper, stirring
slightly	until
mixed.
Serve over hot buttered toast. Serves 4.

title: butter bars
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Bake at 360° until brown, or for about 25 minutes.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In large kettle, combine potatoes, water, onion, celery, carrots, parsley flakes and bouillon.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Meanwhile, gradually add milk to flour, mixing until well blended. Add milk mixture to vegetables and cook until thickened.
Add cubed Velveeta.
Stir until melted.
Serve and enjoy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: granola
directions: Combine oats, wheat germ, oat bran, sunflower seeds, soy nuts, almonds, cinnamon and nutmeg in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine honey, margarine and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients. Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes until nicely, lightly browned. Stir every 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Then add butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients. Drop with spoon in sifted confectioners sugar.
Roll in sugar, then place on cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: shoestring tuna salad
directions: Mix vegetables, eggs and tuna together. Chill.
Fold in shoestring potatoes at the last minute.

title: french fried shrimp batter
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Dip shrimp and fry until golden brown (at 375°).

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat egg yolks, then add sugar and mix.
Add milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in egg whites and fruit to first mixture. Place in churn.
Place ice in churn.
Add salt on ice and churn until stiff.
Cover top of churn and let it set for approximately 30 minutes.

title: easy way dinner bread
directions: Place in this order in mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
(Batter will climb beaters, just push it down with a rubber spatula.)
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Let rise in warm place for 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Makes one loaf.

title: quick spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; mix together in a large bowl with all other ingredients.
To cook, spoon batter into well-greased muffin tins and bake immediately at 425° for 20 minutes.
This batter will keep for several days stored in refrigerator.
You do not have to wait for them to rise.
Yields 24 rolls.

title: tapp's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all but the last two ingredients.
Add 1/2 can chicken broth (or water).
Put into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with corn flakes and margarine.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes, then uncovered for 10 more minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Crumble and brown hamburger; drain.
Layer noodles, hamburger, cottage cheese and sauce.
Repeat for 2nd layer.
Finish with Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese on top.
Pour 1 cup water around edge.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Set aside. Combine oil, eggs and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix well with mixer. Gradually add dry ingredients into creamed mixture, stirring until all ingredients are moistened. Stir in strawberries and chopped pecans (optional).
Spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool bread for 10 minutes, then remove from loaf pans.

title: broccoli ham cheese brunch casserole
directions: Place cubed white bread in 9 x 13-inch pan; layer cheese and ham on bread.
Place broccoli flowerets on ham and cheese.
Beat eggs and milk, onion, salt and mustard; mix well and pour over bread, ham, cheese and broccoli.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes then serve.

title: cherry cider
directions: Combine cider and cinnamon stick in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add jello and stir until dissolved. Serve very hot.
Can be cooled and reheated.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Bake in slow oven at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and bake for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in salted water; drain and mash with potato masher.
Add grated cheese (save some to sprinkle on top).
Add milk and egg that have been beaten together and crushed crackers. Pour in shallow dish; sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle on reserved cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: italian chicken
directions: Dip boneless chicken breast in milk, then in Italian bread crumbs.
Brown chicken lightly in oil, then drain off excess oil. Mix tomato soup and Italian seasonings (to taste) in a separate bowl.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and lower heat to simmer 45 minutes to an hour.
Put a small amount of shredded mozzarella cheese over chicken to melt just before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
(Boneless is best.)
Pour half of stuffing into a 13x9 inch pan.
Drizzle half of butter over stuffing.
Tear chicken into pieces and layer over stuffing. In a separate bowl, combine soups (not diluted).
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Add remaining stuffing mix.
Drizzle remaining butter over top.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl.
Knead until mixture forms soft dough.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in deep casserole dish.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese, then bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple butter
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot and turn to high.
Cook most of the day, then the last hour or two remove the lid of the crock-pot and cook to desired consistency.
If keeping for later or winter use, place in jars and seal, then process in hot water bath for ten minutes.
When the jars are cold remove the rings and store in cool dry place.

title: wedding cake
directions: Mix well. Bake all of your life for 1 happy marriage.

title: ruth's hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients and drop by teaspoon into hot cooking oil.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Drain
oranges
and prepare Dream Whip; set aside.
Mix jello and water; add orange sherbet and mix until melted.
Add oranges and pineapple and fold in Dream Whip.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill two to three hours.

title: beef baked beans
directions: Brown beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in a large pot; cover well with water.
Boil until chicken slips from bone easily.
Tear into small pieces. Mix flour, salt and pepper in a bowl; add milk and stir until smooth.
Replace chicken in pot; add oil, bring to a boil and then spoon in the dip batter into the water.
Boil for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until done.
Remove from heat.

title: chinese candy
directions: Melt chips in microwave or double boiler.
Pour over noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let cool until hard.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: olive oil chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch round pan.
In medium size bowl with fork, stir together flour, granulated sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; blend well.
Pour cake batter into greased pan.
Bake cake 30 to 35 minutes or until center of cake springs back when gently pressed.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Turn cake out onto cake plate and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serves 8.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Requires no icing.

title: kreplach
directions: Mix flour, eggs, water and salt; knead well.
Don't let dough get dry.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick on a lightly floured board.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Place a heaping teaspoonful of filling on each square.
Moisten edges lightly with water; fold over diagonally to form triangles.
Press edges firmly together with fingers or fork.
Let dry.
Kreplach can be frozen at this point.
To serve, boil in lightly salted water for about 20 minutes; drain.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all this together with mixer.
Then add 2 cups Cool Whip and mix again.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla and flour.
Sift flour before measuring.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter.

title: chicken juanita
directions: Mix together onion, green chiles, mushroom soup, chicken soup and milk or chicken broth.
Mix together in pan.
Layer a large casserole or 2 small ones:
quartered corn tortillas, chicken, liquid mixture, cheese (end with cheese on top).
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.
May be frozen before cooking.
Allow longer baking time.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Flatten with floured fork on the cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Remove at once from pan when done.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Stir all ingredients except cranberries and nuts in pan until moistened, then beat for 1 minute.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes. Cool.
Remove from pan and drizzle with glaze consisting of 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 3 teaspoons of orange juice mixed.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons oil in large pan.
Sear round steak (cut into 1/2-inch cubes) until lightly browned.
Add 1 tablespoon oil, garlic and onion.
Cook until wilted.
Add oregano, chili powder, cumin and red pepper.
Mix well.
Add broth, tomatoes, paste, sugar and salt.
Mix.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours until meat is very tender.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: snowball cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 13 x 9 pan. When cool, punch holes in the cake (can use a straw for this). Top with crushed pineapple.

title: surprise carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 round pans (9 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat all ingredients except carrots, pecans and frosting in a large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in carrots and pecans.
Pour into pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean; cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool layers completely.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together until crumbly the oleo, cake mix and one egg. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream until fluffy the cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes until golden brown and cut into squares.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Combine sliced apples with sugar mixture.
Put into pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust to seal the crust together.
Cut slits (about 4) in top.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30-40 minutes or until apples are tender and crust is golden brown.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix in eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix
well.
Add
apples,	raisins, carrots and nuts. Mix well.
Bake
at
350° for 20 to 30 minutes in paper muffin cups.

title: manhattan supper soup(ground beef cabbage soup)
directions: In a large kettle, cook meat until it loses red color.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1 hour, uncovered.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients
and bring to a boil.
Turn on low and cook for five minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and nuts. Beat until starts to thicken.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, using your hands until everything is well mixed and a dark brown color.
Pinch off little balls of the mixture, about the size of a cherry, and roll in additional confectioners sugar.
This will make about 3 dozen. Keep tightly covered.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove and let cool.
Mix 3 cups sugar, eggs, Wilson milk and vanilla.
Add cooled chocolate to this and mix.
Pour into ice cream freezer. Fill with milk.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Dredge steak in flour.
Saute in oil or butter in saucepan.
Saute peppers and onion.
Brown flour in pan and put meat and vegetables back in pan.
Add chicken stock or other liquids.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini cookie
directions: Beat zucchini, soda, sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add eggs, flour, spices and nuts; mix well.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Coarsely chop cabbage and carrot.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into the cabbage mixture.
Chill until serving. Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add sugar.
Stir in milk (just enough to remove lumps).
Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Pour batter into dish.
Spoon fruit into center of butter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until cobbler is risen and lightly browned.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Line an 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil. Butter foil and set aside. In a heavy saucepan, melt chocolate chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt. Remove from heat. Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread evenly in prepared pan. Chill 2 hours or until firm. Turn fudge onto cutting board. Peel off foil and cut into squares. Store covered in refrigerator. Yields about 2 pounds.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together and line bottom of pan.
Grease a 9 or 10-inch spring mold pan or angel food tube pan.

title: chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Debone and skin chicken breasts. Butter a baking dish and place chicken breasts snugly in dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add melted butter, wine and chicken broth.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, covered.
Mix dry tarragon and liquid from chicken; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and mayonnaise into tarragon mixture.
Blend well. Add cut up chicken; mix well.
Add walnuts, if desired.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and put into large casserole. Bake at 300° for about 2 hours.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix all.
Add 1 ($2.29) bag of cheese flavored taco chips, crumbled.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes until bubbles. Put mild Cheddar cheese on top.
When cheese is melted, let cool a few minutes.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Mix cake as package directs.
Pour batter into greased, preheated waffle iron.
When batter stops steaming, remove. Immediately sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix water, salad dressing and vanilla together.
Mix dry ingredients; then mix all of it together.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: seasoned kidney beans
directions: Soak the kidney beans overnight in water; drain the beans. In fresh water, boil the beans until tender; drain.
Slice the Bermuda onion and the red pepper.
Add the sliced onion, sage, red pepper, vinegar and olive oil to the beans.
Ready to serve.

title: ben's giardiniera
directions: Dice the celery, carrots and peppers. Put in a steel bowl and mix. Cover with a thin layer of salt. When all the salt is melted, rinse the vegetables with white vinegar.
After rinsing, put vegetables in a bowl. Cover with red vinegar.
(If you want you can dilute a little, the vinegar.)
After 15 minutes, drain the mix real good.
Chop garlic and parsley.
Add to mix. Add oregano and mix. Fill jars to 1/2-inch from top. Add vegetable oil and top with olive oil. Secure the caps. Turn upside down and store in a cool dark
place. Can be served in 3 weeks.

title: creamed shrimp
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and cream; cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Add green pepper, pimento (cut into thin strips) and shrimp.
When hot, add beaten egg yolks; cook a moment and add seasonings.
Serve on patty shells or toast.

title: freezer candy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 6 logs about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll in shredded coconut.
Cover with wax paper and freeze.
When frozen, slice and serve.
Keep frozen.

title: chicken in tomato sauce
directions: Wash, clean and peel the chicken.
Put on about 4 cups of water to boil.
Put in 1 teaspoon of salt.
Put the chicken in until it is cooked well-done.
When all is done, put the chicken aside.

title: baked corn
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 450°.

title: stuffed chicken breast dijon
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray large 1 1/2-inch deep baking pan with Pam spray.
Place breasts, skin side down and bake 20 minutes. Prepare Stove Top stuffing to box directions and set aside.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight.
Cook 1 hour.
Mix all other ingredients together and stir into drained cooked beans. Put in crock-pot and cook 4 to 6 hours on high.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: new applesauce walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round cake pans.
Put dry cake mix, butter, applesauce, eggs and cinnamon into large mixer bowl.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in black walnuts.
Turn batter into pans and spread evenly.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use Mocha Frosting.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; add onions.
Cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Might prefer more chili powder. I like it this way.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Prepare corn bread mix according to package directions.
Pour batter into greased 11 x 7-inch dish.
Place hot dogs on top of batter.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes or until done.
Combine ketchup, water, pepper, onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat 5 to 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
After removing dish from oven, sprinkle top with cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Serve with sauce.

title: chocolate banana cupcakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Bake in cupcake liners at 350° for 25 minutes.
Great with chocolate frosting.

title: sunset yogurt salad
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Measure 1 cup of gelatin into medium mixing bowl; chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in yogurt.
Pour into medium serving bowl.
Chill until set, but not firm.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Crush cookies; spread 1/2-inch thick in 9 x 13-inch pan. Reserve a few to sprinkle on top.
Combine butter, sugar and eggs. Beat well.
Place on top of crumbs; spread pie mix on top.
Whip cream and spread on blueberries.
Sprinkle with remainder of crumbs.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: jello-fruit and nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Let set approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
When firm, spread with sour cream.
Pour remaining mixture on top and chill until set.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover chicken with water; boil approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour (bring to a boil and then turn to medium-low heat).
Let cool, then debone.
Strain the broth and wash the pot.
Put deboned chicken back in broth and bring to a boil.
Add cut up strips of tortillas a little at a time.
Stir.
Add can of cream of chicken soup; stir until dissolved.

title: pork or beef barbecup
directions: Cook roast until it falls apart.
Then make sauce in a separate pan.
Stir together mustard, celery salt and brown sugar.
Add vinegar, ketchup, onion, clover and bay leaves.
Simmer 20 minutes. Take clover out.
Pour sauce over meat and cook on low in crock-pot for several hours.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
May use as a frozen dessert or salad.
May use other kinds of pie filling.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ham and swiss sandwiches
directions: Cut ham and cheese in small pieces the size of roll.

title: no peek stew
directions: Layer meat, vegetables and potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cornstarch, salt, sugar, pepper, V-8 juice and water.
Pour over stew.
Cover tightly with foil and cook 4 hours at 250°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix as for bread, putting potato with eggs.
Use as wish. Round up remainder, grease and cover with waxed paper and a damp cloth.

title: breader for chicken fillets
directions: Shake together in Ziploc bag.
Shake chicken in flour mixture. Dip in milk.
Shake off excess milk.
Dip in flour mixture again. Fry in small amount of oil.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese and sour cream. Spread on a flat tray.
Top with taco sauce and add chopped lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and black olives. Serve with chips.

title: muffin surprise with honey butter
directions: Preheat oven to 425°,
grease 12 (2 1/2 inch) muffin cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in baking dish, then top with bread crumbs and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: dora's bread pudding(old-fashioned)
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth texture.
Pour into greased loaf or square baking dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: no cook strawberry-raspberry jam
directions: Thoroughly crush strawberries with potato masher; do the same with raspberries.
Measure a scant cup of each of the berries. Stir mixed fruit and sugar until well blended.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir together liquid pectin and lemon juice; bring to boil.
Stir liquid pectin mixture into berry mixture until well mixed.
Continue heating and stirring 3 minutes.
Ladle into 5 (8 ounce) glass or plastic freezer containers, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover with lids.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours or until set.
Store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks or in freezer up to 1 year.

title: turkey salad sandwich filling
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Can be covered and refrigerated for several hours to allow flavors to blend.
Makes great filling for pita pocket sandwiches.

title: spicy apple bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut in bars or squares.

title: snow clumps
directions: Melt chocolate and add peanut butter; mix well. Add rest of the ingredients. Drop on wax paper in a cluster. Let cool until hardened.

title: walnut vegetable medley
directions: Conventional:
In covered skillet over medium heat, in 1/2-inch boiling salted water, cook carrots 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain.
In skillet, stir soup, milk and basil until smooth.
Add broccoli.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Top with walnuts.
Makes 6 cups of 12 servings.

title: mary's strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: Heat Jell-O and pineapple in saucepan until Jell-O dissolves. Set aside.
When cool, add other ingredients.
Pour into a large glass salad bowl.
Chill until set.
For smaller amount half the ingredients using a small can of crushed pineapple and adding 1/4 cup water.
May be used as a salad or dessert.
Other flavors may be used.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine and mix 4 cups whole wheat flour, 2 cups white flour, wheat bran, wheat germ, brown sugar, salt, granulated sugar and quick rising yeast.
Add molasses, shortening and water.
Mix and beat well.
Add additional flour as needed. Continue to mix well.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound fillets until they are thin.
Lay out flat and sprinkle with parsley.
Top each fillet with a slice of cheese, then 1/2 slice of ham.
Roll up tightly.
Stir together mayonnaise and water in a shallow dish.
Roll each chicken fillet in the mayo mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Arrange the rolled fillets, seam side down, in a single layer on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix in order.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust and bake for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: In soup pot, saute the celery, carrots, and onions in the oil over low heat for about 5 minutes. Do not brown the vegetables. Add the potatoes, broccoli, water, butter, salt and black pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium high.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour with 1/2 c. milk or cream. Mix until smooth.
Add to soup and stir.
Add remaining milk or cream. Taste and adjust seasoning, if needed.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg well.
Stir in pineapple.
Add flour, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Mix in nuts.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Layer each of the dips in order, ending with sour cream mixture.
Top with black olives, green onion, tomatoes and grated cheese.
Dip and eat with chips of your choice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs, one at a time. Mix well after each addition.
Add carrots, mix well.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Grease pan and flour lightly to prevent sticking.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 10-inch tube pan at 325°.

title: chicken fettucini
directions: Heat oil in a large saute pan.
Add bacon and saute until most of the fat has softened.
Add chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Continue to saute until bacon is cooked.
Add garlic, thyme, zucchini and chicken stock.
Turn heat to high and cook for 1 minute.
Add cream and cook until mixture starts to thicken.
Add tomato, spinach, fettucini and cheese.
Bring mixture back to a boil.
Toss well and turn out onto serving plate.
Garnish with additional cheese.
Makes 2 (large) servings.

title: corn flake wreaths
directions: Melt together butter and marshmallows.
Mix together vanilla and food coloring and add to first mixture.
Pour over or onto corn flakes and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and shape into wreath shape.
Use red hot candies for center of cookies.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder; stir well.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Gradually stir in water.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll on a floured surface into 6-inch circles. Cook on ungreased skillet over medium heat until lightly brown on both sides.
Serve with your favorite meat, vegetable or egg filling.

title: barbecues
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Sear and add a small amount of water. Cook slowly until tender.
Cool and remove meat.
Shred meat into small pieces.
Thicken meat broth until it is the consistency of thin gravy.
Add celery, onion, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and ketchup.
Add sauce to meat.
Simmer until thick.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs and vanilla and pour over first mixture.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: new potatoes in dill cream sauce
directions: Cut potatoes into quarters; place in a large saucepan, and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium, and cook 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Mix cream cheese, milk and green pepper in a large microwavable bowl.
Microwave on high 40 to 50 seconds, or until cream cheese is melted; stir until well blended.
Stir in fresh dill.
Add drained potatoes; toss lightly to coat.
Makes 16 servings, about 1/2 cup each.
(Cover and refrigerate any leftovers.
Serve as a cold potato salad, stirring in a small amount of milk to thin, if necessary.)

title: king castle pie
directions: Cream well and put in graham cracker crusts or in regular pie crusts that have been baked and cooled.
Makes 2 pies.

title: tex-mex chicken
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken.
Arrange kidney beans and corn in a 3-quart shallow casserole.
Place chicken over the vegetables.
In a bowl, combine the salsa, tomato paste and oregano leaves; spoon over the chicken.
Cover; bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until the chicken is done.
Garnish with chopped fresh tomatoes and sliced avocado.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.
Good served with green salad, cornbread, tortilla chips and fresh fruit!

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into ball. Can be rolled in finely chopped pecans or left plain.

title: asparagus ham roll-ups
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and cook until thick.
Gradually stir in milk and cook until bubbly and thickened.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Place 3 asparagus spears on each ham slice.
Roll up; fasten with toothpicks if necessary.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; cover with cheese sauce.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
I serve this as a main dish.

title: baked custard
directions: Heat milk.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and salt.
Add hot milk slowly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a Pyrex casserole (1-quart). Set in pan of cold water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(Pour through a strainer.)

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine jelly, chili sauce and mustard in crock-pot; stir well.
Cover and cook on high.
Combine remaining ingredients thoroughly. Shape into 30 small meatballs.
Place on broiler rack. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, drain.
Add meatballs to sauce. Stir well to coat.
Cover and cook meatballs on low in crock-pot for 6 hours.
Serve on wooden picks for appetizers.

title: karin's hot stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems.
Chop stems and saute lightly with onions.
Add 1 cup broth.
(You can make broth with cubes of bouillon or Maggi seasoning.)
Mix in stuffing until mixture is stiff.
Season to taste.
Stuff the caps with this mixture. Arrange them in a baking dish.
Pour 2 cups of vegetable stock over them; don't let them dry out while cooking.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: noodles divine
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Add cheese, sour cream, milk and Worcestershire.
Mix well.
Blend in onion, garlic and seasonings. Turn into shallow baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered.
Top with tomato wedges. Bake, uncovered, until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: fritos salad(this amount makes a large salad)
directions: Do not substitute on beans or dressing.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn and milk into already mixed other ingredients.
Stir once during cooking.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: special cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add sour cream, eggs (one at a time), sugar, salt and vanilla.
With beater, mix all well until smooth and creamy.
Layer package of crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread over bottom and close all perforations with fingers.
Do not bring rolls up side.
Pour cheese mixture over roll bottom.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon and a few currants (baby raisins).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until firm in center (test with a toothpick).

title: banana-ginger muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put muffin cups in muffin pan.
In a bowl, mix bananas, syrup, orange juice, applesauce, ginger and lemon. In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Add banana mixture to dry mix and stir; don't overstir. Spoon batter until cups are 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 muffins, 137 calories each, fat .4 gm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar, molasses and vanilla together in large bowl.
Combine flours, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture; mix well.
Add shredded zucchini, nuts and raisins; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour in a preheated 350° oven.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Soak bread in water for 2 to 3 minutes, then squeeze out moisture.
Combine soaked bread with remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Form in small balls (about 20).
Brown slowly in 2 tablespoons hot olive oil.
Add to sauce and cook for 30 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Heat until hot 4 cups milk, sugar and Milnot.
Then let cool. In separate bowl, mix remaining 4 cups milk, vanilla pudding and vanilla.
Shake well.
Add to first mixture and put in ice cream freezer.
Freeze as directed by ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: pineapple icebox dessert(letitia obert's recipe)
directions: Heat milk; add pineapple and whipped cream.
Cover bottom of pan with crushed graham cracker crumbs.
Pour mixture over crumbs. Let stand in refrigerator until needed.
Serves 15.
This can be made 2 days before needed.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic and pepper.
Spread evenly in 9 to 10-inch pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, onion and green pepper. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Serve with crackers, bagel bits, pita chips, vegetable strips, etc.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream sugar
and
Crisco, then add eggs, one at a time. Add remaining
ingredients.
Bake
at
for about 1 hour. Simple and really good!

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl.
Blend in butter, sour cream, eggs and vanilla, beating on low speed; beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Frost only if desired.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Wash the rice. Add to the ground beef.
Mix together with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning. Shape into small balls.

title: tomato dish casserole
directions: Cook tomatoes, onion, salt, sugar, paprika and pepper in pan for 5 minutes.
Arrange tomatoes, eggs, cheese, crumbs and butter in alternate layers in an uncovered casserole.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Cook sausage in water for 20 minutes.
Add Bloody Mary mix and all other ingredients and simmer for one hour or more.
Serve with good crusty bread and a salad for a great dinner.

title: kielbasa bean soup
directions: In large pot or Dutch oven, bring vegetables and water to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add kielbasa and bean soup.
Heat thoroughly.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni with water, oil and salt for 5 to 7 minutes. Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain and return to pot.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Add to macaroni.
Toss together well.
Turn into serving bowl.
Chill.
Add a bit of milk if you want it more moist.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soups and milk and pepper.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, arrange layers of potatoes, onions, cheese and soup mixture. Dot with oleo and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 more minutes.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Spread evenly into a 9 x 12-inch or larger Pyrex dish.
Bake at 450° until brown, about 10 to 17 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: easy taco salad (mexican)
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain well. Stir in taco seasoning. Combine beef, lettuce, tomatoes, dressing, corn chips and cheese in a large serving bowl. Toss well to mix. Serve immediately. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend well.
Serve with strawberries, apples, nectarines or any fresh fruit.

title: homemade chocolate frosting
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and milk in a saucepan.
Heat over a medium flame, stirring frequently.
Frosting is ready when a drop of mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Do not overcook! Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and butter.
Cool by stirring (about a minute or two). Spread evenly over cake.
Work fast, mixture hardens quickly.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Lightly brown chicken in butter.
Add celery and onion, pepper, salt and chicken broth.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until celery is tender.
Add vegetables, mushrooms and water chestnuts. Simmer for 2 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in soy sauce.
Add to chicken mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Serve over hot rice.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; let sit overnight.
Serve with Bugles or other chips.

title: crunchy cheeseroni
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soups, green pepper, pimentos and cooked macaroni.
Place half the mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with half the cheese and onions.
Top with remaining macaroni mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining onions and bake for 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, put in greased 2-quart dish. Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Pour 1 stick oleo (melted) over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy crust apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples into 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix 1/4 cup of sugar with spices and sprinkle over apples.
Melt butter; stir in flour, 1 cup of sugar, egg and chopped walnuts.
Spread over apples.
Place pie plate on cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: salsa fish
directions: Place fish steaks in casserole dish. Cover with salsa, then sausage, then cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.

title: melting moments
directions: Mix together flour, cornstarch and sugar.
In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat butter until creamy; add vanilla and then add flour mixture until well blended.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Shape into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Melt oleo in cake pan.
Coat pan with oleo and drain into a cup and save.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut into pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and oleo together; spoon over cake with spoonfuls scattered around cake.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. "b's" fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit and stir in dry jello and mix well; add cherries. Toss all together and chill in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cheat cake
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve one cup of juice (add water to make one cup).
In saucepan, mix gelatine, milk and juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, to dissolve gelatine.
In large bowl, beat cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Gradually beat in hot gelatine, vanilla and lemon juice.
Chill until mixture holds a kiss shape when dropped from a spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add Equal.
Fold egg whites and drained pineapple into cheese filling mixture.
Turn into 9-inch pie plate or spring-form pan. Chill until firm (3 to 4 hours).

title: corn bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add the milk and egg to the creamed mixture.
Combine the dry ingredients and add to the liquid mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes to 1 hour in bread pan.

title: sausage-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove sausage from casing.
Crumble into a pan and saute until meat is cooked.
Add onion, chopped mushroom stems and garlic.
Saute until mixture is relatively dry (about 10 minutes). Take off heat.
Stir in olives, parsley, chives and beaten eggs, salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Arrange onion and potatoes in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole with the soup mixture.
Salt and pepper; dot top with butter and cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and form a loaf.
Put in loaf pan and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: wally's chicken livers caruso
directions: Using an electric frypan, cook onions, celery and peppers in margarine on low heat until almost soft.
Add 1/2 of the chicken broth with cornstarch and the chicken livers.
Simmer until the livers are cooked through.
If dry, add more broth.
Serve over hot rice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and soda, salt and cinnamon.
Blend in the carrots, walnuts and flavoring.
Pour in a large greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting if desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Next, blend vanilla, oil and sugars, then add eggs.
Finally, stir in the flour, oatmeal and nuts.
Preheat oven to 350° and spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Drop the dough onto the sheet with teaspoon.
Bake until done, about 15 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil and peel, cut in cubes.
Make enough brine to cover beets in kettle.
First boil the brine, add the beets, bring to boil again.
Put sprig of dill in each jar.
Pack beets and cover with brine.
Seal jars tightly.

title: crusty fat-free bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups lukewarm water in large mixing bowl. Add salt and sugar, mixing well with a wooden spoon.
Beat in enough flour, 1 cup at a time, to form a smooth ball that cleans side of bowl.
Cover and set in warm place free of drafts for 1 1/2 hours or until double in size.
Stir down, then turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead a few turns, then cut in half.
Shape each half in a loaf pan.
Sprinkle cornmeal over loaves.
Let rise 5 minutes, then slice tops in 4 places with sharp knife.
Brush with water and put in cold oven with pan of boiling water on bottom rack.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: light and airy dessert
directions: Cook juices; add sugar, flour, eggs and salt.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Combine fruits, acini de pepe and pudding mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, fold in Cool Whip.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all together.
Cover with ice and soak 3 hours.

title: apple-cranberry celebration bread
directions: Mix and sift the flour, baking soda, salt and spices; set aside.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, alternating with grated apples and liquid.
Stir in cranberries and walnuts.
Turn mixture into a greased 11 1/4 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Remove bread from pan or pans.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: sandy's bread pudding
directions: Fill a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan with dried bread, etc.
Combine all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour over bread crumbs and let stand 15 minutes.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: barker's baked chicken
directions: In a shallow baking pan, melt butter.
Stir in honey, mustard and seasonings.
Add chicken.
Coat on all sides.
Bake, skin side down, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces.
Baste. Continue baking until chicken is tender (about 15 minutes).
Makes about 6 servings.

title: sure shot beans
directions: Render bacon in frying pan until most of fat is out of it. Do not overcook.
Put aside.
Pour beans into an 8 x 8-inch ungreased baking pan.
After smoothing evenly, add brown sugar. Sprinkle water over top. If necessary, little drops of water can be added.
Now bacon is set on top.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes, until beans get bubbly.
Make sure bacon does not get too crisp or burn.
Cool for 5 minutes, then ready to serve.
Bottom of pan is quite hot.
Beans can be reheated.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: In a large casserole, make a layer of dressing mix and chicken, then green beans.
Repeat layering until all ingredients are used.
Heat cream soups in a saucepan with small amount of milk until heated through and well combined.
Pour soup mixture over layers in casserole.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: nut bars
directions: Combine ingredients in given order.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: danish puff
directions: First
stage:
Cut
stick
oleo

cup flour, sprinkle
with 2 tablespoons water and mix with a fork.
Round into a

and divide in half.
Pat dough with hands into 2 long
strips (4 x 12-inch).
Place about 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender. Run on high until smooth and frothy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and clams with a little of the clam juice. Add Worcestershire sauce and onion powder.
Serve with veggies.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add pecans and cook 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Makes several dozen.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Roll out and cut.
Bake at 375°.
Makes about 3 dozen small cookies.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix above ingredients (except chicken) in pan chicken will be baked in.
Add chicken; spoon mix over chicken.
Cover with foil and marinate overnight.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda and cocoa with milk and coffee mixture. Beat until well blended.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 layer pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Do not overbake.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and salsa.
Refrigerate. Serve with taco chips.

title: apple nut cake #1
directions: Beat oil and sugar in large bowl of mixer.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour gradually with soda, salt and vanilla.
This will be a very stiff dough.
Add the beaten egg whites and nuts.
Beat until dough is thinner.
Fold in by hand the apples, chopped fine.
Add spices and baking powder.
Bake at 350° in a long 13 x 9-inch pan for 40 minutes or longer.

title: mrs. sees fudge
directions: Combine the sugar and evaporated milk to make a syrup.
Pour hot syrup over chocolate, butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Heat slowly for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Chill and serve with chips or vegetables.
Makes 3 cups.

title: denver biscuits
directions: In large bowl, beat 5 cups flour, sugar, oil, yeast and milk.
Mix well and let rise in warm location, free from drafts for about 1 hour.
Beat down with spoon or mixer.
Sift together remaining ingredients and knead into dough.
Roll and cut into biscuits. Freeze on cookie sheets, then place in plastic bag.
Store in freezer to use as needed.

title: cherry or blueberry delight
directions: Cream the milk and cream cheese.
Add confectioners sugar, then add Cool Whip and nuts.
Set aside.
Slice angel food cake 1/4-inch thick.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Ovens may vary; adjust temperature.
Fruits, nuts and/or candy, coconut, etc. may be added to the dough.
This cookie can also be iced.
Be creative!

title: bistro chicken
directions: Stir together Miracle Whip and seasonings.
Place chicken on grill.
Brush with 1/2 cup sauce.
Grill 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining sauce.

title: four fold delight
directions: Mix together flour, margarine, chopped nuts. Press into 9 x 13 in. baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees. Cool completely.

title: grilled fruit
directions: *Fruits:
Destone apricots, nectarines, plums and peaches.
Cut in half.
Grill, cut side first.
Mangoes can be cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Cherries can be pitted and skewered.
Strawberries can be skewered.
Melons can be cut in bite-size pieces.

title: caulicheese
directions: Strain and break cauliflower into pieces, then make 1 recipe of white sauce.
Put margarine and cornstarch in a pan; stir until melted.
Beat in milk, a bit at a time, until it has a custardy consistency (use a wooden spoon for this).
Add salt, pepper and mustard; pour over cauliflower in baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and golden brown.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Melt margarine in water. Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture pulls away from the sides of the pan and forms a soft ball. Remove from heat and add 1 egg at a time, mixing good with a spoon after each addition. Spread this mixture into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes (prick any large bubbles with a knife as it bakes). Cool.

title: lemon and lime jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-Os. Refrigerate until chilled (not set), syrupy, then whip. Chill 1 can of mix; you will need 1 cup. When chilled, whip, then add mayonnaise, cottage cheese, pineapple, horseradish, lemon juice and walnuts. Mix well. Pour into 9-inch dish. Chill until set.

title: christmas pudding
directions: Break up bread in pieces.
Pour milk over bread.
Put bread and all other ingredients in a baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup brown sugar over top.
Add bits of butter over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Spread butter on bread (cubed bread).
Mix all ingredients. Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Combine broccoli and broth in crockery cooker.
Cover and cook on low heat for 1 to 2 hours (2 to 3 hours if broccoli is frozen). Stir in remaining ingredients until blended and leave vegetable mixture in crock until ready to serve.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 60 calories.

title: apple grape punch
directions: In a large pitcher, combine juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Serve over ice.
Serve with grape or apple slices.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine oil and sugar.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to this mixture; mix well.
Fold in applesauce.
Add floured nuts and raisins.
Bake in floured and greased tube pan or 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° (maybe longer).
Cake is done when middle of cake can be pressed and springs back.

title: chocolate cracks
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt onto wax paper.
Combine sugar, butter and water in large saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until butter is melted.
Stir in chocolate morsels and partially melt.
Remove pan from heat and continue to stir mixture until chocolate is completely melted.
Pour into large bowl; let stand about 5 minutes to cool some.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Bring first four ingredients to boiling and remove from heat. Sift together next three ingredients.
Cut shortening into flour. Add milk all at once.
Stir until moistened.
Roll on lightly floured board.
Cut into six (6-inch) squares.
Place peeled, cored and pared apple in each square.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg and wrap.
Place in baking pan.
Pour syrup over dumplings. Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon-garlic chicken barbecue
directions: In a blender, add oil, lemon juice, salt, oregano, garlic and pepper.
Blend until smooth.
Place chicken pieces in large bowl and pour marinade over chicken and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Drain chicken and reserve marinade for basting. Prepare charcoals for barbecuing.
Grill over medium coals until tender, brushing occasionally with marinade.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate-cherry sundaes
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Measure 1/2 cup of the gelatin into small bowl.
Add cold water; set aside.
Spoon ice cream into remaining gelatin, stirring until melted and smooth. Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Chill until set, but not firm, about 10 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans; set aside.
In medium bowl, stir thawed strawberries, eggs and oil.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Add strawberry mixture to dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Turn loaves out and cool completely.
(A little sugar could be sprinkled lightly on berries over and above that called for in recipe.)

title: chicken curry salad
directions: Mix the ingredients well and add to rice mixture when the rice mixture is cold.
Blend well and put into serving dish. Cover and chill, overnight if desired.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Freezes well.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 30 minutes. Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: chocolate egg cream
directions: Mix half glass milk with chocolate syrup.
Add seltzer!

title: fruit salad for forty
directions: Drain juice off of fruit and save it.
Put all fruit in a bowl, except strawberries.
Pour pudding (powder mix) in bowl with fruit. Add juice and mix until thick (may or may not use all of the juice).
Add strawberries on top.
Chill overnight.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover.
Chill 2 hours. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork dipped in sugar to form crisscross pattern. Bake 9 to 11 minutes at 350° until edges are brown.
Remove to a wire rack; cool completely.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix in bowl flour, sugar, oleo and chopped nuts.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 370° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Soften cream cheese.
Beat in powdered sugar and fold in 1/2 of 9-ounce package Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread on crust when cooled.
Beat until thick pistachio pudding and cold milk.
Spread on Cool Whip and cheese mixture and refrigerate for 30 minutes, then spread remaining 1/2 Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: refrigerator biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes. Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt in a bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add 1 cup buttermilk.
Mix well. Stir in yeast and remaining 1 cup buttermilk.
Knead on floured surface.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Dip into butter. Place on baking sheet.
Let rise for 1 hour or longer. Bake at 400° to 425° for 5 to 10 minutes or until brown.
(May store dough in refrigerator in airtight container up to 1 week.)

title: dipped chocolate
directions: Mix all together.
Make into balls and dip in melted chocolate.
Very good!

title: oven-fried fish
directions: Crunch on the outside, moist on the inside.
Is sure to please.

title: cinnamon raisin bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt and nutmeg.
Add milk, raisins and butter; mix well.
Stir in bread cubes.
Let stand 5 minutes or refrigerate overnight.
