Place into a greased pan (1 1/2-quart) and place into a 13 x 9 pan filled with water.

The water should be about halfway up the sides of the pudding pan. Bake in a 350° oven until puffed and golden brown and a knife inserted in the center of the pudding comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In bowl, cream butter and shortening until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with applesauce, mixing well.
Add corn syrup, raisins and chopped nuts and transfer to greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or more.

title: good ole ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in an ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: play dough
directions: Put on stove on medium heat.
Cook, stirring, until mixture forms into a large ball.
Remove and stir until lumps are removed. Color with food coloring.
Store in plastic bag or airtight container.
May be doubled or tripled.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine pumpkin, eggs, oil and water.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Mix well. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with cream cheese, delicious.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and brown sugar together and let stand for 15 minutes.
Mix white sugar, vanilla and almond brickle chips.
Mix well.
Add to the cream cheese and brown sugar.
Chill about 8 hours or overnight.
Serve with red and green sliced apples; be sure to coat apples with fruit fresh to prevent apples turning brown.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Blend jello, hot water and juice.
Add 1/2 cup cold water, sugar and cheese. Set aside.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Beat egg.
Add fruit cocktail with juice.
Add sifted ingredients and stir together.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch greased pan.
Top with brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Bak at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Combine margarine, water, shortening and cocoa in saucepan. Bring to a boil and pour over sifted sugar and flour.
Mix well. Add buttermilk with soda added, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 X 12 pan that has been sprayed with PAM or greased and floured.
Bake at 350 for 40 minutes.

title: spinach company casserole
directions: Cook spinach or broccoli according to package (microwave) directions.
Do not overcook.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower 4 minutes.
Slice water chestnuts and mix remaining ingredients.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can bake then freeze.

title: mustard chicken
directions: Saute 10 minutes butter, mushrooms, mustard, wine and milk. Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Prepare pasta.
Serve with sauce.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until barely tender.
Mix sauce ingredients; pour over hot carrots, which have been drained.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Marinate overnight or longer in refrigerator.
Drain before serving.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and reserve grease.
Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Add reserved liquid to bacon drippings along with potatoes and onion.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Add corn, soup, milk, salt and pepper; heat thoroughly.
Serve.
Crumble bacon over chowder in bowls.

title: lemon chicken fettuccine
directions: Prepare fettuccine for 4 servings according to directions. While cooking, prepare chicken.
Melt butter in a medium-size heavy skillet.
Sprinkle chicken with salt substitute and lemon juice, cover, reduce heat and cook chicken about 6 minutes. Uncover and brown chicken slightly.
Remove chicken and keep warm. Add wine and scrape skillet and add cream.
Simmer, stirring constantly until volume is reduced by half.
Arrange fettuccine on serving platter, add chicken and pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: molasses cookies (chewy)
directions: Combine flour, soda and cinnamon.
Cream brown sugar and margarine.
Add molasses and egg.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well but don't overbeat.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Let cool slightly and enjoy.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Cook all ingredients except popcorn 4 minutes on High.
Stir and cook 2 more minutes.
Pour over popped corn in bag and shake well.
Place bag in microwave and cook on High 1 1/2 minutes; shake and cook 1 1/2 minutes. Shake and cook 45 seconds.
Shake and cook 30 seconds.
Shake.
Pour onto cookie sheets or flat surface to cool.
Store in airtight container if there is any left to store.
This is delicious and fun to make.

title: the very best brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine the melted butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add the eggs, one at a time, blending after each addition.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix just until combined.

title: black and white raspberry koffee
directions: In a small saucepan, heat milk or half and half over low heat until warmed through.
Divide the white chocolate between 2 large mugs.
Add hot coffee and stir briefly.
Stir brandy (optional) if desired.
Pour half of warmed milk into each mug.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with chocolate.
Makes 2 good-size servings.

title: classic chicken and grape salad
directions: Cut the chicken breasts in 3/4 to 1-inch chunks. Toss the chicken, celery and grapes together in a large bowl. Season with thyme, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Bind the salad with the mayonnaise.
You want to use a lot of mayonnaise to make the salad very moist and creamy.
Transfer the salad to a serving bowl and refrigerate, covered, at least 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O with the boiling water.
Add the sugar.
Let set up partly. Add the remaining ingredients.
Put in mold and refrigerate.

title: russian tea
directions: Simmer cloves and cinnamon in hot water for 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: steak with gravy(for slow pot cooking)
directions: Place cube steak into slow pot.
Mix onion, water, chicken soup, mushrooms and pepper together; pour over steak.
Cover and cook on low for 6 hours.

title: fudge ice cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 4 or 5 minutes until smooth.
Pour into greased 9-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frosting is optional.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling evenly over bottom of pan.
Cover with a layer of pineapple and juice.
Spread cake mix over mixture (no additional liquid is called for).
Dot with butter; sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms.
Leave small ones whole.
Combine all other ingredients in a large jar.
Cover and shake well, then add mushrooms and gently roll them around in the marinade. Refrigerate overnight.
Let stand, rolling jar occasionally for several days for best results.

title: east indian cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for the chutney.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, spread the chutney on top of the ball and serve with crackers.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together in large bowl the sugar, brown sugar, shortening, and peanut butter.
Add egg, milk, and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, and salt.
Mix the ingredients at low speed of mixer until dangle forms. Shape dough into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10-12 minutes.
Immediately top each cookie with a candy kiss or star, press down firmly until cookie cracks around the edge.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook pasta in salt water; drain.
Cut up vegetables and mix, except tomatoes.
Put tomatoes in just before serving.
Pour Salad Supreme over vegetables.
Set in refrigerator overnight. Put Italian dressing on just before serving.

title: groovy bars
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients and spread into 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat together cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Spread on bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (325° for 50 minutes for glass pan).
Cool.
Cut into small squares.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until firm and crust is brown.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Mix beaten eggs and cottage cheese.
Add chopped spinach, cornbread mix, salt, oleo and onion.
Spread into a Pyrex dish (1 to 2-quart size) or any type of desired pan.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.
It needs to be brown and crusty.

title: carrot bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Add bran.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and add oil, sugar and molasses. Add carrots, flour mixture and raisins.
Fill 24 greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Can be served or frozen.

title: 3 day sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake like the directions say.
Cool the cake and cut layers into two to make four, then ice.

title: chicken wings in coke
directions: Place chicken in shallow casserole dish. Sprinkle with garlic and onion salts. Pour mixture of coke, sugar and soy sauce over chicken. Bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours or until liquid has evaporated and becomes sticky.

title: broccoli spears italienne
directions: Partially thaw broccoli spears.
Spread out in a baking dish. Sprinkle with the dressing on top of the broccoli.
Cover tightly with the foil and bake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Choose chicken parts of your choice.
Wash and place in a
13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon soups over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Cook about 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and return to oven to brown.
Delicious served with rice.

title: chicken barley soup(low-fat)
directions: Put all ingredients in 6-quart pressure cooker. Fill with water to 3/4 full.
(May use chicken or turkey stock, or add a bouillon cube if desired.)
Cook under pressure for 15 minutes. Run cold water over pressure cooker until pressure releases, or just remove cooker from heat and let pressure release slowly.

title: chili dip
directions: In bottom of quiche dish, spread softened cream cheese, top with can of chili and top with shredded cheese.
Bake in a microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: flu brew
directions: Add some Coltsfoot if you have a cough.
Add Cottonwood buds to give it expectorant qualities.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull berries; use 1/2 cup berries to mash.
Mix mashed berries and remaining ingredients in small saucepan. Slowly bring to boil, stirring constantly.
When thickened, remove from stove.
Set pan in ice water to cool down.
Arrange berries in baked crust; spoon sauce over berries.
Refrigerate pie approximately an hour before serving.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Place bacon strips on top.
Bake for 1 hour, uncovered, at 375°.

title: easy gingerbread
directions: Mix together soft shortening, sugar and egg.
Blend in molasses and boiling water.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Stir into liquid.
Pour into 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into 3-inch squares. Makes 9 servings.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter; beat together until fluffy. Slowly add confectioners sugar and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Heat peas and water to boiling stage in 2 qt. sauce pan; boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour. Cut bacon into 8 pieces. Stir bacon, onion, and hot pepper into peas. Heat to boiling stage; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until peas are tender (1 to 1 1/2 hours). Stir in rice (uncooked), salt and pepper. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally until rice is tender (about 25 minutes). Stir in additional water if necessary to cook rice.

title: fun taco salad
directions: Tear lettuce and chop tomatoes and onion.
Mix with cheese and corn chips.
Brown ground beef in a large skillet and drain well. Put kidney beans in this and simmer.
Mix ground beef into salad with taco sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve at once. Serves 6.

title: special mushroom sauce for meat loaf
directions: Melt butter; add garlic and parsley.
Add mushrooms and saute. Pour butter and juice out of pan.
Burn sherry wine off, put juices back in pan and thicken.

title: italian sausage stew
directions: Put all in baking pan; cook about 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: bourbon slush(for a crowd)
directions: This is a delicious frozen punch for an outdoor party or wedding.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Combine oil, margarine and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, starting and ending with flour.
Add milk with flour.
Add vanilla or lemon. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Sometimes it takes longer.

title: florentine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir in vinegar, mayonnaise and salt.
Cool until firm. Beat, then add spinach, onion, celery and cottage cheese.
Chill in a 9-inch square pan and cut into squares.

title: hot tomato sauce
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Add vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil for about 25 minutes.
Put into large glass jar and refrigerate.

title: fluffy yogurt pancakes
directions: Use a hot griddle.
Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients in order as listed.
Turn over before bubbles break.
Makes approximately 1 dozen 4-inch cakes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in two 10-inch cake pans.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken with a little salt and pepper.
Dice tomato, green pepper and onion.
Shred chicken.
Mix chicken and vegetables; add corn oil and vinegar to taste.
Dash with salt and pepper.

title: wild rice almondine
directions: Fry sausage until almost done.
Add celery, bell pepper and onion; saute until transparent.
Pour off grease and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a large, greased casserole dish.
Bake for one hour at 350°.
(Bake for 40 minutes, covered, and 20 minutes uncovered.)
Serves 8 to 10.

title: garlic soup
directions: Mash garlic as fine as possible.
Add flour and saute in butter.
Add soup stock and boil for 15 minutes.
Strain and return to fire.
Add seasoning.
With soup at a boil, slip the eggs in gently one at a time so the yolk does not break.
When the eggs are poached, serve the soup with one egg in each bowl.
Add parsley and cheese on top.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all but 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Put in casserole dish and top with rest of crumbs.
Bake one hour at 350 degrees.

title: fried rice
directions: Pour
oil
in
skillet; add green or dry chopped onions and celery.
Stir
a
few minutes.
Add cold rice and sprinkle with soy sauce until light brown.
Stir about 3 minutes.
Push rice to sides
or 1 side and break egg or eggs into pan.
Cook while stirring
with fork.
When eggs are set, mix all together.
Add other choices.

title: zip quick cherry crisp pie
directions: Pour filling into 8-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with cake mix and pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Saute sausage and onion until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes and chilies; simmer 15 minutes, then add cream cheese and sour cream and heat until melted and smooth.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add onion and saute until clear.
Add broccoli, stir thoroughly.
Add cream of mushroom soup and simmer several minutes.
Add cooked rice and Cheez Whiz.
Put in casserole and bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fiesta dip
directions: In large frying pan, brown chuck with yellow onions.
Drain and set aside.
Mash kidney beans and mix with chili powder and catsup.
Combine meat and bean mixture; transfer to chafing dish. Mix red onions, ripe olives and green olives; spread over meat mixture.
Top with cheese and bake at 325° until cheese is melted. Serve in chafing dish with chips.
Serves 12.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add orange juice and sherbet.
Beat with a mixer until melted and smooth.
Chill until thick.
Stir in oranges.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions (minus vanilla).
Mix cream cheese and sugar into Dream Whip.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: artichoke dip(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours or overnight before serving.
Serve with Sociables or Melba rounds.

title: chocolate mint squares
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Cool slightly.
Mix flour and sugar and stir into chocolate mix.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a 9 X 9 pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Place roast in cooking bag. DO NOT FOLLOW DIRECTIONS ON BAG. Mix soup, seasoning, garlic and butter. Pour into bag.

title: frosted jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and stir in 7-Up.
Drain pineapple (save juice) and mix with marshmallows and bananas. Stir in jello and chill until firm.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Sift together last 5 ingredients.
Grease and flour a jelly roll pan (10 1/2 x 15 x 1-inch).
Set oven at 325°.
Mix eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into prepared pan and bake 30 minutes or until done.
Do not overbake!
Cool, frost and cut.
These freeze well frosted or not.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into freezer can.
Add whole milk to fill to freezer line.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and white pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles. Add cooked potatoes and heat through.
Season with chives. Serves 8 to 10.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix well flour, sugar, walnuts, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
In a small bowl, beat egg, crushed pineapple (with its liquid), milk and margarine or butter; stir egg mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened. Pour batter into a greased pan.
Bake for 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool bread.
(Can be made as muffins, also.)

title: soy sauce oven ribs
directions: Turn oven on 350°.
Clean and cut ribs.
Place in a baking pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour over ribs.
Cover dish with foil. Bake 30 minutes.
Uncover dish.
Turn ribs over.
Let ribs remain uncovered and cook 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburg; add kidney beans, soup and sauce to a big kettle.
Add
onions,
vinegar,
sugar,
salt and pepper, plus chili powder.
Cook slowly.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place stick of butter in casserole dish.
Heat in oven at 350 until melted.
While butter is melting, heat fruit in saucepan. Meanwhile, mix flour, sugar, and milk.

title: cookies and cream
directions: Combine 1 cup cookie crumbs, pecans and margarine.
Press into 7 x 11-inch baking dish and place in freezer.
Melt candies in milk in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently.
Let cool to lukewarm.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Refrigerate until firm. Form into ball and roll in pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: easy mexican dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
In mixing bowl, combine beans, taco sauce, tomato sauce and onion.
Set aside 1 cup of corn chips and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Add remaining cheese and corn chips to bean mixture.
Add meat to mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and spread top with sour cream.
You may swirl sour cream into mixture.
Sprinkle top with reserved cheese and chips.
Return to oven for 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pistachio pineapple delight(diabetic recipe)
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into bowl.
Add the mix.
With a wire whisk, rotary beater or electric mixer at lowest speed, beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping and nuts; spoon into dessert dishes.
Pudding will be softset and ready to eat in 5 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings. One-half cup equals 1 bread serving or 80 calories.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Shred beef in into bottom of shallow casserole.
Wrap 1/2 piece sliced bacon around each chicken breast.
Place on top of beef.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Blend soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: triple decker chocolate pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a buttered pie pan (this makes the crust for pie).

title: georgia summer salad
directions: Arrange fruit on lettuce lined plates; serve with Peachy Dip. Yields 12 servings.

title: hot wings
directions: Mix wet ingredients in large bowl.
Cut tips off wings. Marinate wings in sauce for 24 hours.
Note:
If needed sooner, marinate 2 hours and baste with sauce while cooking.

title: twice-baked picante potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in a 400° oven until tender, about 50 minutes. Cool 10 minutes; cut in half.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shells.
Combine potato pulp, picante sauce, margarine and green onions; mix well.
Spoon into reserved shells; place on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven; bake 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and potatoes are hot.
Serve with sour cream and additional picante sauce.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Mix margarine, flour, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Yields 1 pie.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Sift together in an ungreased 8-inch square pan the flour, salt, baking cocoa, baking soda and the granulated sugar.
Make 3 holes in your dry ingredients and put the vanilla in a hole, the vinegar in a hole and the oil in a hole.
Pour 1 cup of water over all and mix well, until flour is gone (can use a hand beater to mix).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute celery and onions in Wesson oil until tender; cook broccoli according to package directions.
Cook rice until tender; drain well.
Combine celery, onions, broccoli and rice; mix well. Add soups and Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Put in baking dish and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour, nuts, sugar and margarine.
Stir well. Stir into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, stirring occasionally to get crispy.
Remove from oven.
Let cool.
Remove from pan onto a dish.
Then put a layer of crumb mixture back in pan.
Drizzle caramel topping over crumb mixture.
Slice ice cream with a knife into blocks to lay in pan to fit.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over top of ice cream. Saran wrap and freeze 3 hours before serving.

title: grandma betty's three bean salad(yields 8 cups)
directions: Put vinegar, sugar, salt and oil into pot and bring to a boil. Put remaining ingredients in large container that can be sealed and put into the refrigerator.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables and mix.
Place in refrigerator.
Let cool for 2 hours before serving.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a large bowl; add eggs and buttermilk, stirring until blended.
Stir in margarine and flavoring and pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: tom thumb cookies
directions: Cream oleo, salt and 1/2 cup of brown sugar.
Add 1 cup flour. Spread on an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: marshmallow meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add marshmallow cream and continue beating until stiff peaks form. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: luby's fish batter
directions: Mix together in large flat pan.
Beat 3 eggs well.
Add 3 tablespoons water per egg and beat again.
Coat each fillet in corn meal, then in egg mixture, then in corn meal mixture again. Drop into hot fat.
Cook until fish is golden brown.
Sift remaining cornmeal mixture and store in freezer in plastic bag.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Beat all ingredients together and put in muffin tins.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Boil chicken for about one hour.
Cool. Tear chicken into pieces.
In a large cooking pot, mix together rice, water and soups bring to a boil, add chicken pieces.	Bring to boil again; then turn down heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: ham stuffed mushrooms
directions: In medium bowl, stir cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in sour cream and dill.
Blend well.
Stir in ham, celery, onion and relish.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time or at least 2 hours.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers in red or green peppers or serving bowl. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: church supper biscuits(serves 100 to 125)
directions: Blend dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles corn meal.
Add water until the mixture handles easily.
Roll out on floured surface to about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place on greased pans and bake at 425° until golden brown, about 10-15 minutes.

title: hot wings
directions: Place chicken wings in a single layer on a baking dish. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper to taste.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Turn
and sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Brush with barbecue sauce.
Bake 10 to 15 more minutes. Turn; brush with barbecue sauce.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes, until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine
salad	oil,
sugar,
hot
water and egg yolks. Beat on	low
speed until well-blended.	Sift together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg,
soda
and
salt.	Add
egg
yolk	mixture, alternating with
carrots
and nuts, to dry mixture, blending well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until they stand in stiff
peaks,
but are
not
dry.
Fold
carefully
into cake batter.	Pour batter into 3 well-greased cake pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: scalloped corn(side dish)
directions: In saucepan, combine corn and milk; heat through.
Gradually stir in egg.
Add 1 cup crumbs, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Pour into greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, 4 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake 6 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and whip topping.
Pour into crust. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and add strawberries.
Chill until thickened.
Pour over cream cheese and chill until firm.

title: lo-cal brocomole
directions: You are richer today than you were yesterday if you have laughed often, given something, forgiven even more, made a new friend, made stepping stones out of stumbling blocks, if you have thought more in terms of thyself than myself, or if you have managed to be cheerful even if you were weary.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: frogmore goulash(beaufort stew)
directions: Fill large stockpot with water until 3/4 full; salt water. Add sliced onion and crab boil.
Bring to boil.
Add kielbasa and cook for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and corn and cook 10 minutes longer.
Add shrimp; stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Do not overcook. Remove when all pink.
Drain whole pot.
Serve on wax paper or newspaper.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Put oil in a frying pan.
Cut up 1/2 of a chicken, then sprinkle in a little four.
Cook the chicken for 20 minutes or until it browns.
Take the chicken out of the stove.
Add tomatoes, carrot, onion, salt and a little pepper.
Cook the vegetables for 15 minutes.
Add chicken and cook for 30 minutes.

title: chicken flautas
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Drain well.
Let stand cool. Shred chicken and add cheese, chili peppers and cumin.
Heat tortillas to soften.
Overlap 2 tortillas by about half.
Spoon about 1/3 cup of chicken mixture down center and roll up tightly. Fry in skillet of oil until crisp and golden brown.
Drain.
Serve on lettuce bed with guacamole, sour cream and salsa.

title: texas delight
directions: Mix together and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until brown.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth; add egg yolks and Eagle Brand milk; mix well.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat egg whites with salt to a soft peak.
Fold gently into yolk mixture.
Place a whole vanilla wafer in each cupcake liner and add mixture.
Bake 30-35 minutes.
Cool. Remove foil liners when chilled.
Serve plain or top with cherry or strawberry topping.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Mash Blue cheese with a little sour cream until well blended. Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Chill and serve with raw vegetables.

title: sugar nuts
directions: Heat, but do not stir sugar, milk and salt to 236° (just above soft ball stage).
Stir in cinnamon, vanilla and nuts (walnuts or pecans).
Stir nuts until sugary on outside. Pour onto wax paper to cool.
Separate.
Enjoy!!!!

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, butter and eggs; blend thoroughly.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add to sugar mixture, alternating with milk.
Mix until dough is smooth.
Drop balls of dough from an ice cream scoop onto a greased cookie sheet or roll out dough, about 1/2-inch on a floured cutting board and cut into desired shapes.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: molasses crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and Crisco together to form crumbs.
Set aside 1 cup of crumbs for the top of the cakes.
Mix molasses, hot water and baking soda together, then beat in the rest of the crumb mixture.
This makes 2 (9-inch) cakes.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup crumbs on top of each cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham fried rice
directions: Saute ham and green onions.
Add bean sprouts.
Add all of the rest of the ingredients.
Heat.
Add soy sauce as desired.

title: mom's homemade vegetable soup
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger; drain well.
In large pot, combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: microwave lemon pie
directions: Put in microwave-safe large bowl and cook 5 minutes (more or less).
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into prebaked crust or graham cracker crust and store in refrigerator.

title: super charged shake
directions: Combine milk, frozen yogurt and peanut butter in a blender. Mix until smooth.
Cut the banana in chunks and add to blender. Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 1 serving.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, stir together all ingredients except chicken wings.
Set aside.
In large roasting pan, bake chicken wings in oven for 45 minutes or until browned. Drain oil from pan.
Pour teriyaki sauce mixture over wings and bake for an additional hour, turning every 20 minutes until fork-tender.
Sauce will continue to thicken after wings are done. Makes about 60 pieces.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Line a baked pie shell with washed strawberries.
In a saucepan, combine the sugar, cornstarch and water.
Add the crushed strawberries.
Cook until clear, then add the butter. Pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream margarine with cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar, milk, pudding
mix
and
Cool
Whip.
Crush Oreo cookies with blender or	food processor.
Start with cookie crumbs.
Layer mixture next;
top	layer will be cookies.	Can be served in a clean flower pot.
Mixture should resemble potting soil.	Have fun!

title: southern fruit pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 300° oven.
Serve with or without whipped topping.

title: faun pie
directions: Cream sugar with oleo.
Mix all ingredients, putting eggs in one at a time.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Brush pie crust with egg white and bake a little longer.

title: potato salad ii
directions: Peel and boil potatoes. Mash hot potatoes until smooth. Drain pickles or relish and add to eggs.
Add enough Miracle Whip or mayonnaise to allow mixture to become easy
to stir (about 1/2 to 3/4 jar).
Add mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover the bowl and refrigerate.
The more time allowed in refrigerator before serving, the better the salad will be.

title: lyn's southwestern beef bake
directions: You will need a 7 x 11-inch or 9 x 9-inch greased dish.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir water, 1/4 cup of the salsa, margarine and contents of vegetable/seasoning packet in 2-quart baking pan.
Stir in stuffing crumbs to moisten.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: cheesy sausage muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs and milk; add to sausage mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased miniature muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Makes at least 2 dozen.

title: homemade chili
directions: Place chili meat and all ingredients into a large saucepan and boil until meat is tender.
Boil slowly.
If you use chili blend, only use 4 tablespoons of chili powder.
The chili pods come in a small package.
Remove chili pod after chili is done.
If chili blend is used, do not use chili powder.
Do not use both.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Place corn flakes in a 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.
In a microwave-safe container, combine sugar and Karo syrup.
Mix, then cook in microwave for two minutes.
Remove and add peanut butter; mix, then cook for one minute in microwave.
Remove and stir well, then pour mixture over corn flakes, then stir.
Let cool; cut into squares and serve.

title: fish in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray foil with Pam.
Put fish in foil. Mix Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce and garlic powder; pour over fish.
Sprinkle with dill weed and lemon pepper.
Seal fish.
Put on baking sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Drain water from orange slices.
Mix into cake mix; blend with mixer for 1 minute.
Bake according to package directions.
Make 4 small layers.

title: old fashioned brownies
directions: Melt shortening and baking chocolate in saucepan.
Mix together egg and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add melted chocolate and shortening to eggs and sugar, mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in small bowl then, slowly add to chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9x9 pan.
Bake at 350° for 22 min.
Recipe can be doubled for 9x13-inch pan.

title: baked chicken salad sandwich
directions: Mix together chicken, olives, mayonnaise, eggs and onion and set aside.
Cream together cheese spread with butter.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Line lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan with half of tortillas. Brown beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning and tomato sauce and cook 5 minutes.
Put half meat mixture on shells.
Spoon cottage cheese mixed with eggs and oregano over meat.
Use other tortillas over cottage cheese and top with the rest of meat.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let sit for 10 minutes.

title: apple butter layer cake
directions: Stir together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves. Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy; beat in eggs, one at a time. Combine buttermilk and apple butter.
Add alternately with the flour mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Bake in 2 greased 9 inch round pans at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
Remove from pans, cool and frost with creamy vanilla frosting.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Cook butter, mushrooms, green peppers and onion for 5 minutes in medium sauce pan. Slowly add flour and cook until mixture is simmering. Remove from heat. Stir in cream, broth and mushroom liquid. Return to heat and heat until boiling, stirring constantly. Add chicken, heat through. Serve over biscuits, noodles or rice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture a little at a time, beating well.
Fold in carrots, raisins and nuts. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: a meaty chowder
directions: Simmer chicken and beef together in water to cover until very well done (about 1 hour).
Cool and remove all bones, skin and excess fat.
Cut up chicken and beef into chunks; return to broth. Add carrots, onions and celery; simmer until tender.
Add other vegetables, tomato juice and noodles.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer until noodles are done.

title: apple cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix together with a spoon. Put in a 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown ground turkey and onion in small amount of vegetable oil; drain.
Add all ingredients except beans and cook 45 minutes. Add beans and simmer 15 minutes more.
Garnish with grated low-fat cheese or jalapenos.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix well.
Shape into long rolls.
Roll in chili powder. Chill.
Slice and serve on crackers.

title: hobo stew
directions: Place small amount of butter in middle of large piece of tinfoil.
Add hamburger patties, potatoes, onions and carrots. Season.
(Can use Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.)
Close tightly.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or on grill.

title: cabbage salad(refrigerated)
directions: Soak the gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Heat the vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Add the gelatin mixture.
Cool to thickened consistency. Whip the salad oil. Stir into other ingredients and store in containers.
Keeps in refrigerator for a long time.

title: baked pineapple filling
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 50 to 60 minutes.

title: elaine's lenty chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bake all for 1 hour at 400°.

title: whipping cream biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on greased cookie sheet with a teaspoon.
Bake in oven at 350° until brown, about 15 minutes or more.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin.
Stir.
Slowly add dry mixture and then water.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
To double recipe, use one whole can of pumpkin.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Prepare noodles per package; drain.
Combine noodles, sauerkraut, corned beef, milk, salad dressing and caraway seed in a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with lid.
Microwave (High) for 10 to 12 minutes, or until hot, stirring once or twice. Top with tomato slices; sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave (High), uncovered, 1 to 2 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: walnut keufels
directions: To make dough, mix the first 3 ingredients with a fork.
Form into 24 small size balls and with fingers, press and shape into small size muffin tins.
Mix the remaining ingredients. Fill muffin tins not quite full. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Be careful, very hot!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put all ingredients except soda in iron skillet or heavy pan like pressure cooker.
Stir and boil until light brown in color. Cut off fire and add 1 1/2 teaspoons soda.
Stir quickly and pour out on buttered cookie sheet (raw coconut makes it even better).

title: unpredictable coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, mix sugar and flour well.
Add eggs then milk, margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into two (9-inch) pie pans or one deep pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until coconut browns on top and pie is set.
No pie crust is needed. Grease pie pan to eliminate pie from sticking to pan.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Layer bottom of pan with coconut (after Pam).
Put pecans on top.
Mix cake mix and pour on top.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, margarine and vanilla.
Pour on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: pam's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage (234°), stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat mixture until blended and begins to thicken.
Spread into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: tropical daiquiri delights(non-alcoholic)
directions: Blend.
Add 1 more can of ice.
Blend until smooth.
May also be frozen.

title: delicious deer burgers
directions: In mixing bowl add all ingredients and mix well.
Fry or broil patties.
While cooking add a little Worcestershire on top of burgers.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Chop tuna fine, then add the gelatin, olives, celery, then stir.
Add the mayonnaise and vinegar and mix well.
Place in a loaf pan and place in refrigerator for an hour or so.
Slice and eat.

title: baked limas(marie's famous)
directions: Cook limas in salt water until tender.
Skim loose skins while cooking.
Drain beans but not until dry.
Mix the above ingredients and pour over limas.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until desired consistency.
Do not overbake; beans have a tendency to thicken more after removing from oven.

title: old-timer custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Mix salt and small amount of cornstarch with sugar.
Add this and flavoring to the egg mixture.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes, then turn over to 350° and bake for another 20 minutes.

title: broccoli with mustard sauce
directions: In small, heavy saucepan, combine egg yolks, 1/4 cup water, mustard, vinegar, sugar and seasoned salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Blend in the garlic spread.
Cool mixture thoroughly.

title: bush's all-american chili
directions: In large pan cook beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned.
Drain excess grease.
Stir in remaining
ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Place brisket on a large stretch of heavy foil.
Sprinkle meat generously with celery, garlic and onion salts.
Pour liquid smoke over meat.
Seal foil tightly and place overnight in the refrigerator.

title: maw porter's mild spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients; mix for 2 minutes with mixer.
Spray pie pan and pour mixture into pan.
Next, arrange the peaches over the first mixture.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar, eggs and oleo for 15 minutes with mixer. Then pour on crust.
Slice bananas and arrange on top of mixture. Top with pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Cover and place in refrigerator, chilling overnight for best flavor.

title: apple pie
directions: Make a 9-inch pastry shell.
Pare, core and quarter apples, then halve each quarter.
Place in large bowl.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and nutmeg (cinnamon) in cup; sprinkle over apples.
Toss to coat well.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Drizzle with lemon juice.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour for topping in bowl.
Cut in butter or margarine and sprinkle over apples.
Slide pie into brown bag, fold open end twice and fasten with paper clips.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in hot oven (425°) for 1 hour (apples will be tender and top bubbly and golden).
Split bag open.
Remove pie and cool on wire rack.
Serve plain, with cheese or ice cream.

title: homemade lite bread
directions: In large glass or plastic mixing bowl, dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Add the sugar and salt; stir until dissolved.
Add flour and shortening.
Mix well until shortening is well blended. Add more flour if needed to make a stiff dough.
Knead dough well on floured surface.
Place dough back into the mixing bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
The next morning, knead dough.
Place into two greased and buttered loaf pans.
Cover with cheesecloth and let double in size.
When baked, brush tops with margarine.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Delicious with butter.

title: mother's cheese cake
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Combine sugar, grated lemon and orange rinds.
Add to cream cheese; beat well.
Add eggs and egg white, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into a 9-inch graham cracker pie shell or spring-form pan.
Bake for 7 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 200°; continue to bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes (longer time for spring-form pan and less time for pie tin).
When ready to serve, top with cherry pie mix, frozen strawberries or any topping of your choice.

title: the wingard family's favorite chicken and noodle dish
directions: Wrap bacon around chicken; salt and pepper.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Cook noodles and broccoli per directions on package.
When chicken is ready, remove chicken pieces from dish and add noodles to soup mixture. Place chicken and broccoli on top of noodles; continue to bake 10 minutes.
Delicious!

title: sun-dried tomato chicken with pasta
directions: Combine tomatoes and broth in small bowl. Cover with vented plastic wrap. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes or until tomatoes are softened. Let stand until cool. Then chop or cut tomatoes with scissors into small pieces. Return to cooking liquid. Spread chicken strips in a microwave-proof 9-inch pie plate. Toss with wine, olive oil and basil. Cover with vented plastic wrap and microwave on High 2 minutes or until no longer pink. Add tomatoes with liquid, spaghetti and shredded cheese. Let stand until cheese has melted. Serves 2.

title: strawberry-pecan cake
directions: Combine white cake mix, jello and Wesson oil.
Add milk and 4 eggs.
After
thoroughly
mixed,
add nuts, coconut and strawberries.
Bake in layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potato flakes according to package directions.
Potatoes can be either hot or cold to measure.
Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Add cream cheese, onion, eggs and flour to potatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in a 9-inch square pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with onion rings. Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions. Mix crackers and cheese together. Mix 1/2 cheese mixture with onions and bake 15 minutes at 350°; cover with other half of cheese mixture and bake another 15 minutes. Top with crushed cracker crumbs, if desired. Makes 6-8 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix chopped pork, chicken, onion, tomatoes and tomato paste. Cook 30 minutes. Add corn and cook until mixture thickens.
During cooking, add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, along with a dash of hot sauce to taste. Stir mixture often, especially after creamed corn is added.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: shoestring salad
directions: Combine tuna, celery, onion and peas.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, milk and celery salt.
Fold dressing into tuna mixture; cover.
Chill several hours.
Stir in shoestring potatoes just before serving.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: In medium bowl, blend cheese and 2 tablespoons of butter until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.

title: jello salad
directions: Stir together Jell-O and fruit cocktail to set.
Stir when partially set.
Before serving, cut up grapes and bananas and mix in with heavy cream.
Cream can be substituted for can cream or Cool Whip but not as good.

title: california chicken
directions: Mix all and put in a casserole, cover with buttered bread crumbs.

title: angelic cream squares
directions: *Add more sugar to vanilla pudding, about 1/4 cup more. Instead of 2 cups of milk for pudding, use 1 3/4 cups.

title: bran muffins
directions: In a blender, crumble Shredded Wheat until fine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Keep covered in refrigerator.
Will keep for a month.
Bake muffins as needed for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: walnut-shrimp salad
directions: Marinate walnuts, shrimp, celery and oranges in French dressing a 1/2 hour before serving.
Chill.
Arrange on lettuce leaves for salad plates.
Sprinkle with additional garlic salt, if desired.
Garnish with watercress.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Prepare Egg Beaters as hard-cooked Egg Beaters.
Combine melted margarine, vinegar, mustard and salt in blender container. Cover and whisk on medium-high speed just until blended.
Without turning off blender, immediately add cooked Egg Beaters, if necessary use rubber spatula to keep mixture flowing to blade. Continue whirling until mixture is well blended.
Use deviled mixture for stuffing celery, cherry tomatoes or hard-cooked egg whites.

title: one-pan stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add soup and water (mixed) and the stroganoff mix.
Stir and boil.
Pour over the cooked noodles. Season and sprinkle with caraway seed.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Spray a baking sheet with nonstick spray. Mix melted butter, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce together. Coat pecan halves with mixture. Sprinkle with red pepper, if desired. Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes. Stir halfway through baking. Remove when crispy. Keep an eye on them, so they don't burn.

title: pecan custard pie
directions: Combine brown sugar and flour.
Stir in melted butter and syrup.
Add well-beaten eggs with remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour filling into a deep dish pastry shell and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Top should be well browned and knife inserted into center should come out clean.

title: mama's ham hocks and corn dumplings
directions: Wash ham hocks.
Place in large pot or pressure cooker; cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Remove ham hocks from broth and cool.
Remove skin and fat, leaving only the lean ham.
Chop ham in small pieces, set aside.
Either use a defatting cup to remove fat from broth or place pot in refrigerator until fat rises to top and hardens, then remove.
When ham broth is defatted, place on stove and heat slowly to a boil.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and egg yolk.
Blend well. Stir in cheese, green pepper, green onion and celery salt.
Beat 2 egg whites (room temperature) at high speed with mixer until soft peaks are formed. Gently fold whites into potato mixture. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart dish coated with vegetable spray.
Sprinkle paprika on top. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 starch.
Contains 89 calories.

title: cinnamon sugar
directions: Mix and place in sealed container.
Use as needed on toast.

title: aunt lorna's persimmon pudding
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Add persimmon pulp. Add flour with baking powder, soda and cloves.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch greased cake pan and bake 1 hour at 325° to 350° until brown and done.
Will be moist and delicious with consistency of brownies.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Partially prepare the batter the night before.
In a small bowl, combine the oatmeal and 2 cups of the buttermilk.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, sift together the flours, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Save broth. Break or cut up chicken. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Cover bottom of dish with Doritos chips.
Add layer of chicken.
Combine mushroom soup, chicken soup, Ro-Tel and can of broth.
Mix together and pour over chicken and chips.
Top with grated cheese.
Alternate layers until all is used. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: brown mountain cake
directions: Cream your butter and sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and warm water.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water with salt.
When soft, run through strainer.
Boil milk with onion; remove onion and add milk slowly to potatoes, mixing well with a whisk.
Melt half the butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed, then stir into hot soup.
Boil one minute; strain and add remaining butter. Sprinkle with parsley.
Thin with hot milk if desired.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Put flour and sugar in a bowl and mix well.
Put buttermilk and soda in a cup and set aside.
Bring to a boil the oleo, Wesson oil, Coke and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture and mix well.
Add buttermilk mixture, eggs (slightly beaten), vanilla and marshmallows.
Put in oblong (9 x 13-inch) greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
When done, ice immediately.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken and cool.
Mix flour, Crisco and salt and take broth to moisten dough.
Heat broth, cream of chicken soup, milk and chicken seasoning.
Have broth boiling and roll dough paper thin.
Drop in boiling broth; do not stir often.
Cook until done. Only use white meat to broth for dumplings.

title: grated raw sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. If desired, add coconut to top before baking.
Bake at 350 degrees until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the soups, water and rice.
Butter a casserole well.
Layer chicken breasts in bottom; pour mixture over. Sprinkle with a package of dry onion soup mix.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dissolve jello well in boiling water.
Add lemon cake mix, then eggs, and oil.
Beat well.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; salt and pepper to taste.
Drain well.
Add tomato soup and green beans (drained).
Place mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Prepare six servings of mashed potato flakes.
Spoon in mounds on top of the casserole.
Brush top of potatoes with whipped egg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: jerky
directions: Cut meat into strips.

title: egg nog
directions: Whip all ingredients together. You can add more or less of each ingredient, depending on your taste and the consistency you prefer.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugars; add well beaten eggs and mix. Add raisins or dates, fruit cocktail, nuts and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets and bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: easy sundae sauce
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and water in saucepan, stirring well.
Cook over low heat until sugar is well dissolved, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking until sauce comes to a full boil. Remove from heat and add butter.
Serve warm or cold over ice cream or cake.

title: chicken gruel
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Slowly pour meal, stirring constantly. This is a thin soup.
Cook on low heat until you think meal is done.

title: quick and easy chinese chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine catsup and next 6 ingredients; stir well and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done, turning over the chicken after 45 minutes and basting occasionally.
Yields 9 servings.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and stir together.

title: meat and vegetable marinade
directions: Mix all in Ziploc bag.
Can place meat and vegetables (squash, broccoli, halved new potatoes, onions, etc.) in a large Ziploc bag. Marinate for 1 hour or more.
Save the marinade for gravy. Add 1/2 cup peanut butter to leftover marinade and cook over medium heat until the gravy is medium thick.
Use over chicken, pork, beef or seafood.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Mix together soup, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, curry powder, pepper and shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate.
Heat oven to 350° (moderate).

Mix melted butter and almonds on cookie sheet and place in oven for about 6 minutes, turning frequently, until almonds are lightly toasted. About 30 minutes before serving time, heat curried shrimp in top of double boiler over boiling water until piping hot. Stir in almonds.
Serve over hot fluffy rice with a fruit salad, if desired. Serve with chutney.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate surprise cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan.
In a small bowl, using an electric mixer, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla, beat until blended and set aside. Prepare cake mix (as label says) and fold in chocolate morsels and walnuts.
Pour chocolate batter into prepared pan evenly.
Cover with cream cheese mixture.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick, inserted in middle, comes out clean.
Cool for 25 minutes and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: aunt hatties meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except the ketchup, syrup and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well and place in baking dish and shape into a loaf. Cover with tinfoil and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Remove foil. Mix last 3 ingredients and spread over loaf. Return to oven and bake 15 minutes.

title: milk chocolate truffles
directions: *You can also use the flavoring oils, 10 drops to 2 pounds.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix thoroughly.
This recipe makes a large batch.
Keeps at least 6 weeks in a covered container in fridge.
When ready to bake, fill lined muffin tins 2/3 full and let set 10 to 15 minutes, then bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine meat and all the other	except preserves.
Make into balls, then spread the preserves on top.
Bake
at	350° for 30 minutes.

title: one step cocoa cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9-inch) round pans.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat 1 minute at low speed to combine ingredients.
Beat for 3 minutes at highest speed.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: good cake(makes a nice birthday cake)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add Crisco.
Cut in with pastry blender or 2 knives.
Beat eggs and milk in another bowl with vanilla. Add to dry ingredient mixture.
Bake in 350° oven about 40 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, salt and syrup together.
Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter; continue cooking on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Mixture should be darkened.
Add baking soda and stir quickly.
Quickly pour out on a lightly greased cookie sheet or aluminum foil square.
Spread thin.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, combine spaghetti, margarine, salt, pepper, egg and Parmesan cheese.
Layer cottage cheese on top. Combine ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic and layer over cottage cheese.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar to spaghetti sauce and pour over ground beef layer.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: shawneetown cake
directions: In a bowl (large), combine eggs and buttermilk.
Beat in sugar, flour, vanilla, cinnamon and soda.
Set aside.
Combine butter or oleo, water and cocoa in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and continue boiling 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add to batter and beat until smooth and well blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Spread evenly with Shawneetown Cake Icing.

title: baked corn
directions: Butter dish with some butter.
Mix ingredients.
Reserve some crumbs for top and dot with butter.
Bake approximately 35 minutes or until set and lightly browned.

title: grilled pizza with red peppers and cheese(makes 4 servings)
directions: Spray the grill grate with nonstick spray and preheat the grill to medium.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add carrots, pineapple and nuts, mixing after each is added.
Bake in 3 layer pans or 1 (9 x 15-inch) sheet pan for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fried apples
directions: Slice and core apples.
In hot skillet have oil and margarine. Put sliced apples in hot skillet and fry for 5 minutes until tender.
Add cinnamon, brown sugar and vanilla and cook for 5 minutes more stirring constantly.
Serve with pork chops or pork roast.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Put lid on and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Take out what you need.
Put in muffin pan and bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
This will keep a week in refrigerator.
Good for breakfast.
I usually leave out dates when using for breakfast.

title: cranberry wassail
directions: Tie cloves and cinnamon in a cheesecloth bag; set aside.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In sauce pan, bring 1 inch water to boil.
Cover.
Prepare parsley, onion, and potatoes.
To boiling water, add onions, potatoes, and 3 teaspoons salt.
Boil 5 minutes covered.
Drain.
In double boiler, over low heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, paprika, and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
In greased 1
1/2 quart casserole dish, arrange 1/3 of potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle half of parsley.
Pour on 1/3 of sauce.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake uncovered for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil; let thicken.
Set aside and let cool completely.
Cut strawberries up into baked pie shell.
Pour strawberry mixture over strawberries.
Cover with whipped cream.
Keep refrigerated.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Saute onions and leeks in butter slowly until transparent but not brown. Add broth and potatoes. Cook until potatoes are soft. Buzz in food processor or food mill. Add salt, pepper and milk to taste. Serve hot or cold. Garnish with finely chopped chives or curry.

title: scramble nut mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in very large roaster or large pans.
Bake in very slow oven (250°) for 2 hours, stirring and turning mixture with wooden spoon every 15 minutes (be careful not to crush cereal).
Yields 9 quarts.

title: sauteed shrimp with garlic and herbs
directions: Place a shrimp flat on a work surface with the tail nearest you.
Hold the shrimp flat with one hand.
Using a sharp paring knife and beginning at the head end, slit 2/3 of the way down the shrimp toward the tail, cutting about halfway through.
Scrape out the exposed vein.
Repeat with the remaining shrimp.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Wash and cap strawberries; mash.
Put fruit in saucepan on high heat and stir until mixture comes to full boil.
Add all of sugar at once and stir well.
Bring to full boil and boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and skim off foam. Ladle into hot jars, filling to within 1/8-inch from top.
Cover and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 8 cups or 9 (8-ounce) jars.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Add rice to chicken broth.
Bring to boil and simmer, covered, until rice is tender, about 20 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: swiss onion steak
directions: Put steak in a baking dish; season well.
Pour onion soup over steak.
Add tomatoes and liquid.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions, until tender.
Drain and set aside.
In a pan melt margarine; stir in flour and brown lightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until thickened.
Pour over green beans and heat 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Cream together, sugar, peanut butter, and vanilla extract. Gradually pour in milk.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, and salt.
Stir into peanut butter mixture.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour 9-inch tube pan.
Mix together flour and baking soda; set aside.
Combine eggs, mincemeat and milk.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Stir in flour mixture.
Pour into pan.
Bake until center springs back when touched and top is brown.

title: texas broccoli and corn
directions: Thaw broccoli; melt oleo and mix with 3/4 herb stuffing mix. Add broccoli, cream-style corn and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup herb stuffing mix on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° to 350° for about 45 minutes or until broccoli is done.

title: texas crab grass
directions: Slowly melt butter in heavy saucepan. Add onion and saute until soft. Add spinach. Add crabmeat and grated cheese.
Transfer to chafing dish and serve with crackers.

title: deviled pecan spread appetizer
directions: Blend deviled ham and cream cheese.
Stir in pineapple, green pepper, onion and 1 cup pecans.
Spoon into a bowl or dish and smooth top.
Sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup pecans on top. Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: mac tuna casserole
directions: Mix milk, soups, garlic and onions together in a pot.
While simmering, add peas, corn, macaroni, tuna, mushrooms, salt and pepper (to taste).
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then top cheese with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place under broiler to brown just before serving.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, save juice; add enough water to make 1 cup. Heat to boiling and dissolve gelatin; cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale.
Chill until partially set.
Blend pineapple and cranberry sauce, then fold into gelatin.
Turn into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Prepare topping as per package directions.
Blend in cream cheese; spread over gelatin.
Toast nuts in butter in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle on top of topping.
Chill well before serving.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed.
While cake is still hot, pour pineapple with juice over it.
Refrigerate cake until cool. Combine cream cheese, milk and pudding; mix well.
Add Cool Whip. Beat one minute or until mixed.
Spread over cake.
Sprinkle coconut over top if you like.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix avocados, onion, chili pepper, lime juice, cilantro, salt and garlic.
Stir in tomato.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: sopaipillas
directions: In medium mixing bowl stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until thoroughly combined.
Gradually add water, stirring with a fork.
Dump flour dough mixture onto lightly floured surface.
Knead dough until smooth (3 to 5 minutes).
Place dough ball in plastic bag to keep moist while making individual sopaipillas.

title: rave fruit dip
directions: Simply blend the yogurt and Cool Whip for a delicious and easy dip for fruit.
Serve with sliced peaches, nectarines, variety of apples and large strawberries, then enjoy the raves. It's low-fat, nutritious and good!
(Kids love it, too!)

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs with small amount of milk.
Beat really good with mixer.
Add remaining milk.
Cook in double boiler until it begins to coat wooden spoon.
Take off stove.
Add the marshmallows.
Stir and when marshmallows are melted, put in jug and refrigerate until cold.

title: mexican chicken salad
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients stirring well; cover and chill. At serving time, add avocado if desired.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix. Bake 30 minutes at 350° in unbaked pie shell.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp and artichoke casserole
directions: Butter oblong baking dish.
Melt 4 1/2 tablespoons of butter. Blend in flour. Add milk and cream; cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Add salt and pepper; set aside. Saute mushrooms in remaining butter for about 5 minutes.
Arrange artichokes in a single layer on bottom of prepared dish;

scatter shrimp over artichokes. Cover shrimp with mushrooms. Stir sherry and Worcestershire sauce into cream sauce and pour into baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°. Serves 6.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Coarsely crush pretzels.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar; mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cream the cheese and 1 cup sugar; blend well.
Add Cool Whip, mixing well.
Spread over cooled pretzel mixture. Dissolve the jello in boiling water; add frozen strawberries breaking up strawberries with a fork as your stir.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Pour over Cool Whip/cream cheese layer. Chill until set.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg and milk to make soft dough.
Roll out to thickness desired and cut into squares.
Drop into boiling chicken broth.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine last 4 ingredients and sprinkle over top.
Continue to bake 30 more minutes or until golden brown.

title: patty's vegetable casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, layer each of the ingredients in order given except oleo and bread.
Do not dilute the soup; spread it out on top of the vegetables.
Melt oleo and soak each slice of bread until all the oleo is absorbed.
Cut or tear bread into small pieces and place on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until bread is browned lightly.

title: okra creole
directions: Cut okra crosswise in 1-inch pieces.
Fry bacon crisp.
Fry okra in bacon drippings.
Remove okra and cook onion until tender, stirring to keep from burning.
Add tomatoes after breaking into small pieces.
Bring to boil, then add okra and bacon mixture and chili powder.
This is good with rice.

title: baked chicken delight
directions: Simmer chicken in water, seasoned to taste with salt, pepper and bay leaf until tender.
Let cool in broth.
Remove meat from bones and place in shallow pan.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Do not let brown.
Arrange onion over chicken.
Sprinkle rice evenly over top and add enough chicken broth to cover.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add mushrooms and cream. Cover and bake another 30 minutes.
Do not stir.

title: betty's lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Saute onions in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Stir into beef the onions, tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: quick mexican casserole
directions: Cook beef in skillet until crumbly and light in color.
Add onions, salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Place 3 cups of chips to bottom of casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Pour meat sauce over that and top with remaining chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: green noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on the package.
Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Add pimentos, salt, pepper, oregano and basil.
Put chicken in a well-sprayed 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Add layers of noodles, cheese mixture and almonds.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: party mix
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Melt chocolate in the microwave.
Pour over mixture and stir - covering all.
Pour onto wax paper or Reynolds wrap.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.
Store in an air tight container.

title: peanut butter fruit dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer until fluffy.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: oreo delight
directions: Will need a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bread pot fondue
directions: Slice off top of bread loaf, reserving top.
Carefully hollow out inside of loaf with small paring knife, leaving 1/2-inch shell.
Cut the removed bread into 1-inch cubes; reserve.

title: stay-abed stew
directions: Mix these ingredients together in a casserole dish that has a tight lid.
Put the lid on and put the casserole in a 275° oven. Cooks by itself and is done in 5 hours.
Stir well before serving. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: susie's pink fluff
directions: Drain pineapple and mix all ingredients together. Chill. You may substitute any flavor of Jello or fruit.

title: apple souffle
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add
sugar, melted margarine and milk. Add crumbs.
Stir in applesauce.
Mix all well.
Turn into greased casserole dish.
Bake
at
for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is set.

title: high protein "meatless" loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl with hands.
Bake at 425° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: sponge cake-trinidad
directions: Mix oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Beat eggs with peeling of lime or orange.
Add eggs and lime peel to sugar and oleo mixture. Add flour and baking powder in 4 parts.
Beat well.
Add vanilla. Beat well.
Remove peeling and pour mixture into well-greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into 9-inch square casserole or into jello mold.
Chill until set.
Spread sour cream over mixture.
Pour remaining over sour cream; chill until set.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: welfare cookies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a sauce pan, bring to a boil. Add peanut butter and stir well. Fold in corn flakes and drop on waxed paper. Press together.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Microwave almond bark on High for 3 minutes.
Add chocolate chips on High for 1 minute.
Add peanuts, mix well and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool and store in airtight container.

title: beef choufleur
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch squares.
Separate cauliflower into flowerettes (about 4 cups).
Brown meat in butter about 5 minutes. Add cauliflower, green pepper, soy sauce and garlic.
Stir lightly to coat vegetables with soy sauce.
Cover pan and simmer until vegetables are barely tender, about 10 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Put corn in buttered baking dish.
Combine eggs, crumbs, milk, salt, pepper and pimento.
Pour over corn; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add sugar to other ingredients.
Add cooked rice and bring to a boil, stirring constantly to thicken rice.
Pour into bowl. Sprinkle with cinnamon and refrigerate.

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, sour cream, cream cheese, chives and garlic powder (can use instant mashed potatoes).
Put this mixture in a casserole dish and top with bread crumbs mixed with melted margarine.
Spread grated Cheddar cheese on top of bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes if potatoes are hot.
For cold potatoes, bake at 350° for 35 minutes, adding Cheddar cheese 10 minutes before removing from oven.
Serves 6.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large pan, cook chicken breasts until done.
Place chicken on plate to cool.
Use chicken broth to cook noodles until done. May have to add more water. Add bouillon cubes with noodles. Chicken should be cool.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add salt and pepper to own liking.

title: nannie's beaten biscuits
directions: Work all well into a stiff dough.
Beat with a wooden mallet or an axe head until blister forms, 30 to 45 minutes.
Make into biscuits.
Prick with fork tine and bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: quick fruit dessert
directions: Layer as written.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat evaporated milk, sugar and eggs well.
Blend in salt, vanilla, corn meal and sugar.
Stir in pecans; pour into pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and continue baking until knife inserted near the center comes out clean, about 35 minutes.

title: tandy cake
directions: Scald milk and butter together and set aside.
Mix eggs, vanilla, salt, sugar, flour and baking powder and add to milk mixture.
Pour into pan.
Use jelly roll pan or 15 x 10 x 3/4-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Heat milk, bread and butter in double boiler until creamy. Remove bones from salmon carefully.
Beat eggs and mix with salmon, salt, milk, bread and butter, stirring well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: marinara sauce with red wine
directions: *Put tomatoes in a blender
and
puree	for 1 minute if you do not want tomato chunks in sauce.

title: mushroom special
directions: Alternate layers of bread, sausage and cheese in a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Beat eggs; add salt and milk.
Pour over casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, add cheese to top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In a large deep pan, saute first 4 ingredients in shortening. Sprinkle with salt; stir in water. Bring mixture to a boil. Add spaghetti. Cook, uncovered, 12 to 15 minutes or until spaghetti is tender. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 minutes to blend flavors.

title: rutabaga(kalrabi)
directions: Peel and cube rutabaga.
Cook in salted water until tender. Drain, then mash rutabaga.
Melt butter; add flour and mix.
Add milk slowly and stir until thick.
Add rutabaga to white sauce and serve.
Rutabaga may also be served without mixing into white sauce.
After mashing, add a little of the salted water and serve.

title: chicken oregano
directions: Place chicken pieces in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook uncovered in 375° oven, spooning oil mixture over chicken occasionally, for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; cook until thickest pieces are done, about 30 minutes more.

title: black raspberry salad
directions: Add water to juice to make 3 1/2 cups liquid.
Add jello.
Set aside 2 cups jello mixture.
Allow to partially set.
Add drained fruit to remaining jello.
Pour fruity jello into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Prepare whipped topping; fold into partially set jello.
Add nuts.
Spread over top of set jello. Allow to completely set.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat milk and butter (can be heated in microwave).
Mix sugar, salt and eggs.
Add 1/2 cup of hot milk to mixture.
Blend well. Add to hot milk.
Cook in microwave on Low heat; stir often, until it begins to thicken.
Remove and add rice and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 300° oven until it sets.
Best served warm.
Add flavoring to custard after taking out of microwave.

title: sunflower seed cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, salt and baking soda; mix well.
Mix in oats and sunflower seeds.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Flatten. Bake 8 1/2 to 9 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool slightly before removing from sheet.
Makes about 7 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, rice, 1/4 cup soup, carrot, onion, egg and 1/2 teaspoon ginger.
Form into 1-inch balls.
