Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until browned.
Drain fat.

title: angel delight
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Gradually add powdered sugar and extract.
Beat until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Set aside.
Cut angel food cake into 1-inch squares.
Fold cake into Cool Whip mixture; add pecans.
Press mixture into 8-inch square container.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: maple syrup pie
directions: Heat together the syrup, milk and butter until butter is melted.
Add mixture of remaining ingredients to hot mixture and boil until thick.
Pour into baked and cooled pie crust.
Top with unsweetened whipped cream.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Wrap each breast in slice of bacon.
Line baking dish with dried beef.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soup with 1/2 can of milk. Pour all over.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Put 1 tablespoon sour cream over each breast and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Good with chicken-flavored rice!

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix 1/2 cup water with mushroom soup.
Slice potatoes into large casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients and place between layers of potatoes.
Sprinkle crumbs and Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at
350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate (devil's food cocoa) cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening mixture until thick.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 1 minute after each addition.
Add cocoa mixture.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately in thirds with sour milk to which the vanilla has been added.
Bake in well-greased and floured layer cake pans or 13 x 9-inch baking dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
If cake is not done, continue baking, checking at 5 minute intervals.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a frypan, spray butter or melt 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine; saute chopped onion.
Add can of Vegeburger and stir until heated.
Grease casserole dish with spray butter or margarine.
Put Vegeburger mix in bottom of casserole.
Top with drained whole kernel corn and creamed corn and smooth lightly. Dollop mashed potatoes around the top and smooth around lightly. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly on sides.

title: bloody mary
directions: Garnish with a celery stalk.

title: light lemon seed bundt cake
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar and 1/3 cup oil in large bowl, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating mixture well after each addition.

title: carrot coins
directions: Scrape or peel carrots and slice into 1/4-inch coins. Cook carrots until tender. Combine carrots with all ingredients while warm. Marinate in refrigerator overnight or at least 12 hours. Serve cold.

title: hungarian cabbage and noodles
directions: Cut cabbage in small pieces, dice onion and mince garlic. Chop bacon into very fine pieces and fry until brown.
Then add onion, garlic, salt, pepper and paprika; let saute a few minutes. Now add cabbage and let saute until cabbage is wilted.
Cook noodles as directed on package, then drain and add to cabbage and bacon mixture.
Put into a baking pan and place in oven on low heat for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple fridge cake
directions: Prepare cake in 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake according to package directions.
Combine crushed pineapple and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil; cool slightly.
When baked cake has cooled, pierce holes in cake with fork.
Pour pineapple mixture over it.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions. Cool.
Spread prepared pudding over top.
Chill.
Just before serving, cover with sweetened whipped cream and sprinkle with coconut.
If desired, garnish with pineapple slices.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese, then egg yolks.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour and soda.
Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in large tube pan in slow oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Spread cooked spaghetti in bottom of large baking dish. Sprinkle all of cheese on top of spaghetti.
Pour and spread sauce on top of cheese and spaghetti.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bring soup, water, mix and Gravy Master to a boil.
Put rice, carrots, onion and pepper in casserole dish.
Add hot mixture and mix.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lalla's apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate wafer and whipped cream cake
directions: On large serving dish, spread whipped cream on back side of cookies and place in a row to cover length of plate.
Continue on to next row, placing side by side.
When all cookies are used, spread remaining Cool Whip over entire rows.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.

title: hard candy
directions: Sprinkle 18x24 inch strip of heavy duty aluminum foil with powered sugar. Mix sugar, corn syrup, water in large heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310°F, or until drops of syrup forms a hard and brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flavoring oil and coloring.
Pour onto foil, cool, break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers.

With the different flavoring you get a different color of candy. Peppermint - pink, Cinnamon - red, Spearmint - green, Lemon - yellow, Wintergreen - Pale green, Orange - orange, Butter - light yellow, Cherry - red, Raspberry - blue red, Chocolate - brown, Butter Rum - yellow brown, Grape - purple, Lime - yellow green.

title: reducing soup
directions: Mix ingredients together and let come to a full boil for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and let the reducing soup simmer for a full 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until vegetables are soft.

title: aunt neoma's egg custard
directions: Stir together flour and sugar; mix in milk, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 250° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Salt chicken and place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup and margarine or sour cream.
Add pepper and paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix well. Pat out 1/2-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into rounds.
Bake at 450°
for 18 to 20 minutes on greased baking sheet.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and green peppers in fat until onions are yellow and almost tender.
Add hamburg and cook until meat falls apart, stirring often.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings; mix well.
Put in a greased baking dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours (until rice is tender).

title: pearl cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift cornstarch with flour 4 times. Resift with baking powder and add little by little to butter and sugar, stirring and blending.
Add milk and vanilla and beat well. Fold in egg whites, stiffly beaten with salt.
Bake in medium sized loaf cake pan at 325° for about 40 minutes.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: amish friendship starter
directions: Combine these ingredients in a large airtight container with lid.
Store at room temperature; do not refrigerate.
Stir this starter every day for 17 days.
For the next 10 days, following the 17, handle the starter according to these instructions:
On day 18 do nothing, on days 19, 20 and 21, stir.
On day 22, stir and add 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar, 1 cup milk and stir again.
Stir on days 23, 24, 25 and 26.
On day 27, add 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar, 1 cup milk and stir.
Take out 1 cup three times.
Give 1 cup each to two friends and keep the remaining cup for yourself and use it in the Amish Bread recipe that follows.

title: beef steak-potato scallop
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut steak in chunks, coat with flour.
Melt shortening in skillet.
Brown meat; add onions, cook and stir until onions are tender.
Pour into casserole dish (ungreased).
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and pepper.
Pour water over mixture.
Cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes or until meat is tender.
Increase oven temperature to 450°.
Arrange potato slices on meat.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Bake uncovered about 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice well.
Add nuts, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix and pour into pie crusts and chill.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll each mushroom cap in small amount of olive oil and place on baking sheet or dish.
Combine remaining ingredients including stems and divide evenly among mushrooms. Bake 10 minutes, just to heat through.

title: parsley rice squares
directions: Mix rice, parsley, cheese and onion together; set aside. Combine eggs, milk, Worcestershire and salt.
Add to rice mixture. Put in rectangular baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy yeast biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Mix well. Remove from bowl and knead 4 or 5 minutes on a floured surface. Roll and cut. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 72 biscuits.

title: apricot supreme cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 10 minutes. Pour into a greased and floured pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: nut roll (povitica)
directions: Add flour in pan or bowl and make a well.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Add yeast after it dissolves.
Knead well after it is well stirred.
Add more flour if it's too sticky.
Let rise, then roll on floured tablecloth or table until thicken.
Add cinnamon all over spread with hand, then add a little more sugar.
Spread all over dough.
After nut filling is scalded on low heat to lukewarm, spread over the dough.
Roll up and seal edges.

title: chow chow
directions: Cover chopped ingredients with 10% brine for 12 to 24 hours. Drain; heat spices to boiling point.
Mix vegetables; stir well and let stand overnight.
Stir in morning.
Pack in sterilized jars.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread in buttered baking dish.
Beat the eggs and add sugar, salt, milk and water.
Stir in vanilla and lemon peel. Pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: toll house cookie pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars.
Combine with margarine.
Let cool.
After cooling, add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Power Level: High.
Microwave Time: 5 1/2 to 7 1/2 minutes total.

title: new york buffalo wings
directions: Deep-fry wings 20 minutes in vegetable oil. Wings will rise to top when done. Drain. Put in bowl. In saucepan, combine hot sauce and margarine. Toss until completely coated. Ready to serve. Serve with cut up celery and carrot sticks with Blue cheese dressing.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Boil hominy for
minutes;
drain and season to taste with garlic salt, seasoned salt, salt and pepper.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Stir
in green chilies, sour cream and onion. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 5.

title: myra's cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add flour and milk alternately to batter.
Add vanilla. Pour into a greased tube pan (and floured).
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Don't forget to put into cold oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except 1/4 cup milk.
Shape into loaf and place in baking dish.
Pour 1/4 cup milk on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: secrets
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients well.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Spread and pack on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips.
Return to oven for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread chips for frosting.
(Cookie sheet must be the kind with 1/2-inch sides.)

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, water and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Quickly stir in chocolate and nuts.
Turn into a buttered pan.
Spread 1-inch thick.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Combine pecans and coconut in a bowl; sprinkle in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan lined with waxed paper.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions; spoon over pecan/coconut mixture.
Combine cream cheese and oleo in a bowl; beat until smooth.
Beat in confectioners sugar.
Spoon over cake batter. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 45 minutes; cut into squares.
Invert squares onto serving plates.
Makes 15 servings.

title: lemon chicken oregano
directions: Combine butter, seasoned salt and lemon juice together.
Place chicken in baking pan; brush both sides with mixture.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes, or until chicken is fully cooked.

title: new york's famous egg cream
directions: (Despite its name, this drink is eggless and creamless.)

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Add 1 box confectioners sugar.

title: corn fritters
directions: Heat cooking oil to 400°.
In bowl with fork, mix 1 tablespoon salad oil and all ingredients just until blended.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into hot oil; fry 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown, turning once.
Sprinkle with sugar or serve with syrup.

title: mom's pecan chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in an unbaked pie shell for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl with fork.
Add pudding, oil, cake mix, water and sour cream.
Mix by hand until blended.
Combine cinnamon, nuts and sugar and set aside.
In 2 loaf pans, put one layer of batter, 1 layer of cinnamon mixture and 1 layer of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: daddy's bread
directions: To flour, add enough water to make a medium to thin dough. Mix well. Cook, covered, in iron skillet in shortening until top of dough is dry. Turn over.
Add another 1/4 cup shortening. Brown and serve hot.

title: marinade(3 to 5 pounds of meat)
directions: Best if meat is marinated overnight.

title: calico rice
directions: Saute peppers and onion in oleo for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except sour
cream.
Bring
to
a
boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer
for
20 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Garnish with sour cream, if desired.

title: corn relish
directions: Grind up cabbage, tomatoes, peppers, and onions. Cut corn from cob. Bring vinegar mustard and sugar to a boil. Add everything and cook until thick, Pour in jars and seal.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and pineapple.
Heat until Jell-O is dissolved.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix well. Put in dish and cool.

title: pineapple - sour cream pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts and chill.
For lighter consistency, can add 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Makes a good pudding, also.

title: chinese cabbage chicken salad
directions: Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil for 1 1/2 minutes (do not overcook).
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper and let cool.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Then let cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add sugar, oil and eggs; beat at medium speed 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in three 9-inch greased and floured pans at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Yields a 3-layer cake.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into 2 loaves or 4 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and place in icebox.
Keeps real well.

title: hank's creamed tuna
directions: Mix all together and heat.
Serve on toast.

title: cooked salad dressing(potato salad)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in top of double boiler. Beat egg with milk; slowly add to dry ingredients, blending thoroughly. Cook over hot water until it begins to thicken, about 5 to 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Add vinegar and butter; continue cooking until thickened, about 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from heat and beat with rotary beater until smooth. Chill. Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: tomato florentine tortellini soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy large saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute 2 minutes.
Stir in broth and tortellini.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Mix in Parmesan and seasonings.
Simmer until tortellini is just tender.
Stir in tomatoes, spinach and basil. Simmer 2 minutes.

title: nana's lime sherbet salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water, then add sherbet and stir until smooth.
Add oranges and pineapple excluding liquid.
Stir and add whipped cream and marshmallows.
Stir well.
Chill until firm.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all together.
Place on lettuce leaves and chill.
Garnish with pickles or sliced bell pepper.

title: marinated vegetable salad 2
directions: Pour cooled marinade over vegetables.
Marinate 24 hours. Drain before serving.

title: cinnamon pull-apart bread
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour mixture over the frozen rolls in a Bundt pan.
Leave in a cold oven overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom parmesan salad
directions: Mix oil, lemon juice and cheese in a bowl.
Add mushrooms; toss to coat.
Add pepper.
Let stand 15 minutes for flavor to develop.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, then mix all ingredients in a 1-gallon crock or other nonmetallic container.
Cover with a close fitting lid and let starter rise until light and bubbly on top (12 hours in warm weather, longer in cool weather). Never let starter get cold.
After each time you use starter, add 1 cup warm water, 2 teaspoons sugar and enough flour to return the starter to its original consistency.
Add more potato as food for the yeast (when original potato is used up), but don't add yeast.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Clean 2 dozen corn cobs.
Cover with water and boil as you would fruit.
Make jelly according to the directions on Sure-Jell box.
Tastes like a blend of apple and plum jelly.

title: cream cheese delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine, pecans and sugar.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Beat until fluffy 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese; pour into cool crust.
Mix pudding and milk and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over mixture and sprinkle some ground pecans over Cool Whip.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add milk, egg and shortening.
Beat entire ingredients together.
Pour into hot greased iron skillet or pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes and top is brown.

title: grandma robbins' pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour mixture into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hillshire farm smoked sausage creole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in oil.
Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil while stirring well.
Cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from stove and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes, together until blended well.
Add potatoes; mix together.
Garnish with bits of beet and white of egg, lettuce, parsley or cress.

title: fruit punch
directions: Pour ingredients into a shaker cup filled with ice.
Shake. Strain over ice into a balloon glass.
Garnish with pineapple wedge and an orchid.

title: tasty squash
directions: In a large saucepan, place squash; on medium heat, boil squash until tender. Drain water from squash. Saute squash in butter, pepper and onion.

title: grasshopper cake
directions: Follow directions for cake mix on the box, but also add 3 tablespoons green creme de menthe.
Bake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Top cake with 1 jar fudge topping, then spread with Cool Whip that has been mixed with 3 tablespoons of green creme de menthe.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: cake doughnuts
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, cornstarch and salt 3 times. In a separate bowl, cream
butter with sugar; add eggs and beat. Add milk alternately with flour mixture. Turn out on a well-floured board and roll to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut into doughnuts. Let stand about 5 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook in oven at 325° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Last half hour, cut strings on meat.
Shred roast with2 forks.
Serve on Italian bread or French rolls.

title: reuben spread
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks.
Add condensed milk and juice; beat until thick.
Stir in lime rind and food coloring. Pour mixture into crust.
Stiffly beat eggs until foamy with cream of tartar.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Spread meringue on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of crust.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Cool. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: bar cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese over low heat in heavy pan; stir in other ingredients.
Pour into 1 or more containers.
Cover and serve chilled.
Great for gift giving in attractive containers.

title: cheese nut loaf
directions: Mix cake mix and salt.
Save some to dust over cheese and nuts.
Prepare according to directions.
Fold in grated cheese and nuts which have been dusted with remaining cake mix.
Pour in a 9-inch loaf pan and bake according to package directions.
Cool loaf on cake rack before storing.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix jello (do not add water to jello as directions on jello package) and pineapple (do not drain) and heat until jello dissolves.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Put in large Pyrex dish and sprinkle top with chopped pecans.
Cool in refrigerator until set.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Remove excess fat from beef brisket.
Rub liquid smoke, celery seed, garlic powder and black pepper on all sides of brisket.
Wrap in heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 200° for 6 hours.
Remove from oven and allow to cool.
Slice into thin slices.
Return slices to foil (in a neat row).
Cover with barbecue sauce and bake for 2 hours at 200° or until heated.

title: almost homemade cream-style corn
directions: Melt oleo in Corning Ware dish.
Stir in corn.
Beat egg.
Add milk, salt and black pepper.
Pour mixture over corn; mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and alternate with sour cream.
Place 1/2 dough in greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Add remaining dough, smooth top and sprinkle with topping (cinnamon and sugar). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Remove and drain.
In same pan, cook vegetables until tender.
Add sausage and cashews.
Cook 2 minutes until warm.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash and leave a little stem on okra.
Place in jars with a clove of garlic and hot pepper and dill.
Heat vinegar, salt and water and pour over okra and seal.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread in mixing bowl. Add vanilla flavoring, milk, spices, sugar, raisins, egg and butter. Melt butter and pour into mixture. Combine all ingredients together. Pour in lightly oiled baking pan. Cook until top of mixture is crisp. When cool, cut up in squares.

title: english drop cookies
directions: Set oven to 325°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs, cold coffee and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet 3 inches apart.

title: cold cucumber walnut soup *
directions: Coarsely chop toasted walnuts; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Taste for seasoning, adding more salt, pepper and lemon juice as needed.
Place half of mixture in a food processor and process until very smooth.
Add to the rest of the mixture and add the walnuts.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: peanut buttery cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine flour, sugar, brown sugar, butter, eggs, salt, baking soda and vanilla. Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Dissolve soda in 1 tablespoon water.
Mix all ingredients. Cook on medium to high temperature using Crisco to fry them.

title: farmer's style chops in crock-pot
directions: Coat chops with flour and brown in oil in skillet. Chops do not have to be done, just brown. In crock-pot, place potatoes and onions. On top of potatoes, place cabbage, salt and pepper. Place browned chops on top and pour in water. Do not stir! Cover and cook on high for about 4 hours or on low for 7 to 8 hours or until tender.

title: mint brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions; cool completely.
Mix and cream well the margarine, powdered sugar, creme de menthe and pudding.
Spread on top of brownies. Refrigerate until well chilled.
Top with canned icing; chill for at least 3 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Stir in zucchini, flour and all remaining dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes and then remove from pans and place on cooling racks.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Refrigerate in glass covered container. Lasts weeks in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers (Melba, Triscuits).

title: pasta gulogua (pasta with garlic oil and tomatoes)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a blender.
Boil 1 pound of desired pasta until cooked.
Drain and pour sauce mixture over pasta, leaving some for the side or to dip Italian bread in. Enjoy!

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crispy baked potatoes
directions: Mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Wash potatoes.
Cut lengthwise into quarters.
Melt oleo in oblong dish in oven.
Roll potatoes in flour mixture.
Place in buttered dish with skin side up.
Bake 1 hour at 350°; turn once.

title: light and crispy waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron.
Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, in small bowl.
Beat on low until moistened.
Increase to medium; mix until smooth.
By hand, gently fold in beaten egg whites. Pour 1/2 cup of batter over griddle.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Note:
The procedure for mixing this salad is most important, to blend the flavors, so please follow procedure accurately for best results.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread coconut on bottom of well-greased 15 x 11 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread pecans over coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed and pour over coconut and pecans.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Line 4 x 7-inch pan with chipped beef.
Roll bacon around each chicken breast and place in pan.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in a 250° oven for 2 hours. Do not cover.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook onion and celery until tender in microwave or in saucepan.
Combine chicken, celery, onion and canned vegetables in baking dish.
Heat cream of chicken soup (plus 1 can water) and chicken broth to boiling point.
Pour over chicken-vegetable mixture.
Mix flour, margarine and buttermilk.
Add black pepper; spoon over chicken-vegetable mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until crust is golden brown (about 50 minutes).

title: hot wings
directions: Fry wing pieces.
Combine hot sauce and butter.
Dip wing pieces in sauce to coat.

title: old fashioned deer sausage
directions: Sprinkle combined seasonings over meat.
Toss until well mixed.

title: blender broccoli soup
directions: For chilled soup, partially thaw broccoli.
Break in small chunks.
Place in blender with 1/2 cup of the milk.
Blend until broccoli is very fine.
Add remaining milk and next 6 ingredients. Blend until smooth, 45 to 60 seconds.
Chill thoroughly.
If you wish for heated broccoli soup, cook the frozen broccoli.
Heat with other ingredients on low heat, but do not let scorch.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and Velveeta cheese, then stir mixture into drained broccoli.
Crush crackers and melt other 1/2 stick of butter into them.
Line casserole dish with 1/5 of the Ritz mixture.
Pour in the "broccoli soup."
Top with the remaining Ritz mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peppy cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage, covered, in 1-quart of boiling water for 7 minutes.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; toss with cooked cabbage.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix powdered
sugar and oleo;
beat well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lola's cheese spread
directions: Mix together.
Spread on English muffins or biscuits.
Heat in 400° oven to melt cheese.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: jumbo molasses cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, shortening, salt, molasses and vinegar. Mixture may look curdled, but add gradually the dry ingredients and spices.
Beat until smooth.
Refrigerate for about an hour. On lightly greased cookie sheets, drop by tablespoon, three inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.
Oven temperature:

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar well. Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients and mix. Chill for 45 minutes or more.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk and water. Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost.

title: people chow for microwave
directions: Mix chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter in microwave. Add flavoring.
Pour chocolate chip mixture over cereal.
Mix until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture in plastic garbage bag with sugar and shake until all is coated with sugar.
Spread on wax paper until cool.

title: lo-cal soup
directions: Combine in large pot, not quite covering with water. Simmer for hours.

title: cheesy breakfast burritos
directions: Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour into skillet.
Cook slowly over medium-low heat until eggs begin to set, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sausage and onion; continue cooking until eggs are set.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Top each tortilla with 2 slices Kraft singles and 1/2 of the egg mixture. Roll up.
Makes 2 burritos.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs and add other ingredients. Mix well. Put in 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry icebox pie
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers 1/4-inch thick in bottom of pie pan or oblong baking dish.
Melt margarine and mix with powdered sugar, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and cook until it thickens, about 12 to 14 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Pour cooked mixture over cookie crumbs.
Spoon thawed strawberries over that.
Top with whipped cream or whipped topping.
Sprinkle a few cookie crumbs on top.
Freeze.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce with sugar and softened margarine.
Add egg. Mix.
Add flour, a little at a time with salt, cloves and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix uncooked rice, water, beef broth, onion soup and Worcestershire sauce in large casserole dish.
Layer top with pork chops, then onion.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: grasshoppers
directions: Put ice cream in a large bowl.
Pour rest of ingredients in and beat with a mixer until well blended.
Pour batter back into ice cream pail.
Put into freezer for 2 days.
Before serving can be served with cherries, nuts, chocolate syrup or can just leave plain.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: old macdonald pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Beat together at low to medium speed: shortening, sugar, eggs, pumpkin and water.
Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture (a little at a time).
Mix well.
Add dates and walnuts. Mix well.
Fill two greased and floured loaf pans 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: skillet stew
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Then top with onion, potatoes, carrots and celery soup (undiluted).
Simmer 40 to 50 minutes, covered, until
potatoes are done.
Top with soft cheese.

title: salsa
directions: Combine tomatoes, garlic, scallions, and chilies in a food processor or blender until coarsely chopped.
Stir in olive oil and lime juice.
Add salt, pepper and cilantro or parsley to taste.
Let stand one hour before serving.
Good on anything.

title: pizza bites
directions: Place crackers on cookie sheet.
Put pizza sauce on crackers. Place pepperoni slices on sauce and then top with Mozzarella cheese.
Put cookie sheet in a 350° oven and bake until cheese is melted.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix tuna in blender or food processor until broken.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until fairly smooth; don't puree. Refrigerate until slightly thickened, about 1 hour.
Serve with whole grain crackers and fresh vegetables.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread crescent roll dough on pizza pan or cookie plate (greased).
Pinch seams together.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Remove from oven; let cool completely. Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing until blended.
Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Cut into wedges or squares.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix
sugar, flour, baking powder, soda and cocoa.
Sift several
times.
Add mayonnaise, cold water and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour
into a loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Ice with Caramel Frosting.

title: bran muffins
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix together eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add in Raisin Bran, flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Pour mixture into muffin tins.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes.
This makes about 6 dozen muffins.
The batter keeps in the refrigerator for 4 to 6 weeks.
Keep tightly covered and use as needed.
Can also make just half the recipe.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake by directions and let cake cool and crumble.
In punch bowl, make 3 layers by alternating cake, pineapple (spoon over cake), coconut, pudding (already mixed), cherry pie filling (save some for topping) and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until served.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: easy cream cheese cake
directions: Mix flour and butter together and spread in a 13x9 pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix ground ham, ground pork, milk, cracker crumbs, onions mustard and eggs and form into egg-size balls; place in heavy skillet or electric skillet.
Mix the brown sugar, water and vinegar and pour over first mixture in skillet.
Simmer all for 1 1/2 hours.
These are great!

title: kool fruity punch
directions: Mix together until sugar has dissolved.
Chill and serve.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Drain noodles, combine with tuna (drained), Miracle Whip, celery, soup and milk.
Pour in 2-quart casserole.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *If using cherry chip or yellow cake mix, decrease margarine to 1/3 cup.
If using marble cake mix, mix in marbling mixture with the cake mix.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Pour half of this mixture in jelly roll pan and reserve half for top layer.
Combine melted butter, pudding mix and milk over low heat for about 1 minute.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla. Beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Spread over chocolate layer and refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Add salted peanuts to remaining chocolate mixture and spread over second layer. Refrigerate.

title: easy manicotti
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion.
Add spinach souffle mix and cool.
Add cheese.
Stuff mixture into manicotti with small spoon.
Add enough water to cover bottom of pan 1/2 inch. Pour spaghetti sauce over noodles and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add oil, egg and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oatmeal, coconut, Rice Krispies and chocolate chips.
Spoon into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust of graham crumbs and melted butter. Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat together for 15 minutes (no less) the sugar, butter and eggs. Spread on the crust. Then slice the bananas; put on top of mixture. Cover bananas with pineapple. Spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle with coconut. Decorate with cherries and chopped nuts on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: Brown onion, garlic and sweet basil in olive oil.
Add salt and pepper.
Add meat and brown.
Add tomato puree, tomato sauce and tomato paste. Fill each can with cold water and pour water into sauce.
Add sugar and bay leaves, stir well.
Cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Uncover and simmer 1 hour more.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: rachel angel's basic cookie recipe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
